            "size": 167966,
            "text": "{\"total_count\":29,\"incomplete_results\":false,\"items\":[{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/47\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/47/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/47/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/47/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/47\",\"id\":4462211523,\"node_id\":\"PR_kwDOSSFOvc7cUN-2\",\"number\":47,\"title\":\"feat(integrations): add StartSessionPoller adapters for github + slack\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"lachiejames\",\"id\":47808687,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3ODA4Njg3\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47808687?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/lachiejames\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[],\"state\":\"open\",\"locked\":false,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":2,\"created_at\":\"2026-05-17T03:57:25Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-17T04:04:33Z\",\"closed_at\":null,\"assignee\":null,\"author_association\":\"MEMBER\",\"type\":null,\"active_lock_reason\":null,\"draft\":false,\"pull_request\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/pulls/47\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/47\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/47.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/47.patch\",\"merged_at\":null},\"body\":\"## What this PR does\\n\\nAdds `createGithubPoller({ token, username })` and `createSlackPoller({ token })` factories in `packages/integrations/{github,slack}/src/poller.ts`. Each returns a `StartSessionPoller` closure (from `@slopweaver/mcp-server`) that reads the current cursor from `integration_state` and threads it as `since` into the underlying sub-polls:\\n\\n- **github** → `pollPullRequests` → `pollIssues` → `pollMentions` (sequential; `username` is captured by the factory)\\n- **slack** → `pollMentions` → `pollDMs` (sequential; identity is resolved per-sub-poll via `auth.test()`)\\n\\nSub-polls run sequentially (not `Promise.all`) so they share each platform's rate-limit budget without bursting; the order also mirrors v1 ranking weight. Boundary translation from neverthrow `Result` to the `Promise<void>` contract happens via `_unsafeUnwrap()`.\\n\\nThe factories are re-exported from each package's public entry; no consumer is wired up yet (that's PR 2 / #45).\\n\\n## Why\\n\\nLays the groundwork for live polling in the `start_session` composite tool — first PR in the v1-wire chain.\\n\\ncloses #44 · refs #2\\n\\n## Test plan\\n\\n- [x] Tests added — `packages/integrations/{github,slack}/src/poller.test.ts` (7 + 6 tests). They mock the underlying poll-function exports via `vi.mock` and assert: call order, threaded args (`token`, `username`, `db`, `now`-as-function, `since` from cursor), and that an `Err` from any sub-poll rejects the closure's promise with the neverthrow `_unsafeUnwrap` wrapper carrying the original BaseError on `.data.value`.\\n- [x] `pnpm validate` green locally (all six gates: `check-service-boundaries`, `format:check`, `lint`, `compile`, `test`, `knip`).\\n- [x] CI green (will trigger on push).\\n\\n## Notes for the reviewer\\n\\n- **`_unsafeUnwrap`, not literal `throw`.** The chain doc and `.claude/rules/error-handling.md` both call this out: `_unsafeUnwrap()` is a neverthrow API that throws on `Err` (which the wrapping `async` function turns into a rejected promise), but it's NOT a literal `throw` keyword, so the `pnpm cli check-service-boundaries` scanner stays green. `grep \\\"throw \\\" packages/integrations/{github,slack}/src/poller.ts` returns zero matches.\\n\\n- **Tests deviate from the chain doc's \\\"Polly-cassette tests\\\" instruction.** The factory signature is fixed at `{ token }` / `{ token, username }` per the locked scope — there's no client-injection point through which to feed a `WebClient`/`Octokit` mock, and recording fresh cassettes for the new test paths would require capturing per-test HTTP against a real workspace. Since the adapters are thin wiring layers and the cassette-backed integration coverage already lives in `polling.test.ts` / `mentions.test.ts` / `dms.test.ts`, the new test files use `vi.mock` at the polling-module level to verify the adapter's wiring contract (call order, arg threading, error propagation) deterministically and offline.\\n\\n- **Each integration package now depends on `@slopweaver/mcp-server`** so the `StartSessionPoller` type comes from the canonical source rather than a duplicated structural alias. `boundaries/element-types` allows package → package; there's no cycle because mcp-server doesn't import integration packages back.\\n\\n- **slack `since` shape.** `pollMentions` / `pollDMs` declare `since?: Date` and the package uses `exactOptionalPropertyTypes`, so `since: undefined` is a compile error. The adapter spreads `{ since: new Date(cursor) } | {}` conditionally instead of passing `since: undefined`.\\n\\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\\n\\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\\n\\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\\n\\n* **New Features**\\n  * Extended GitHub integration with polling capabilities for pull requests, issues, and mentions.\\n  * Extended Slack integration with polling capabilities for mentions and direct messages.\\n\\n* **Tests**\\n  * Added comprehensive test coverage for GitHub and Slack integration pollers.\\n\\n* **Chores**\\n  * Added new dependency support for both GitHub and Slack integrations.\\n\\n<!-- review_stack_entry_start -->\\n\\n[![Review Change Stack](https://storage.googleapis.com/coderabbit_public_assets/review-stack-in-coderabbit-ui.svg)](https://app.coderabbit.ai/change-stack/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/47?utm_source=github_walkthrough&utm_medium=github&utm_campaign=change_stack)\\n\\n<!-- review_stack_entry_end -->\\n\\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\",\"reactions\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/47/reactions\",\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"timeline_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/47/timeline\",\"performed_via_github_app\":null,\"state_reason\":null,\"score\":1},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/43\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/43/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/43/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/43/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/43\",\"id\":4461679737,\"node_id\":\"PR_kwDOSSFOvc7cSpKo\",\"number\":43,\"title\":\"docs: refresh CODEBASE_MAP.md after #34, #35, #36, #40, #42\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"lachiejames\",\"id\":47808687,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3ODA4Njg3\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47808687?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/lachiejames\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[],\"state\":\"closed\",\"locked\":false,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":1,\"created_at\":\"2026-05-16T23:51:20Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-17T02:31:12Z\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-05-17T02:30:17Z\",\"assignee\":null,\"author_association\":\"MEMBER\",\"type\":null,\"active_lock_reason\":null,\"draft\":false,\"pull_request\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/pulls/43\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/43\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/43.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/43.patch\",\"merged_at\":\"2026-05-17T02:30:17Z\"},\"body\":\"## What this PR does\\n\\nRegenerates `docs/CODEBASE_MAP.md` (last mapped 2026-05-03) to match the current tree. Also fixes two stale claims in `CLAUDE.md`.\\n\\n## Why\\n\\nSince the last map, five PRs more than doubled the repo from 93 files / 65k tokens to 214 files / 175k tokens:\\n\\n- #34 — `slopweaver connect github` / `connect slack` subcommands\\n- #35 — `start_session` composite tool\\n- #36 — `packages/ui` (Diagnostics page on `localhost:60701`)\\n- #40 — testing + code-quality rules and reviewer agents\\n- #42 — repo-wide migration to `Result`/`ResultAsync` (neverthrow via `@slopweaver/errors`)\\n\\nThe map's \\\"Future apps (not yet present)\\\" section is now obsolete (the `slopweaver` binary exists), the package list missed `errors`, `env`, `ui`, and the three integration packages, and the `start_session` ranking/staleness rules weren't documented.\\n\\n`CLAUDE.md` previously said the published binary \\\"does not exist yet\\\" and referenced phantom `packages/auth/` and `packages/memory/` directories — fixed.\\n\\n## Test plan\\n\\n- [x] `pnpm validate` passes (six gates green: check-service-boundaries, format:check, lint, compile, test, knip)\\n- [x] `gitleaks` pre-commit hook clean\\n- [x] Cartographer regenerated the map via five parallel Sonnet readers (foundation / integrations / mcp-server + mcp-local / cli-tools / ui)\\n- [x] Verified all file paths referenced in the map exist in the worktree\\n\\n## Breaking changes\\n\\nNone — docs-only.\\n\\n## Notes for the reviewer\\n\\nDiff is large (≈541 insertions / 323 deletions in `CODEBASE_MAP.md`) but it's a full regeneration. The `CLAUDE.md` change is small and surgical (two sections updated).\\n\\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\\n\\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\\n\\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\\n\\n## Release Notes\\n\\n* **Documentation**\\n  * Updated architecture and project structure documentation with comprehensive details on tooling, workspace packages, and component organization.\\n  * Expanded codebase mapping with explicit entry points, module behaviors, and operational workflows to improve developer understanding of the system architecture.\\n\\n<!-- review_stack_entry_start -->\\n\\n[![Review Change Stack](https://storage.googleapis.com/coderabbit_public_assets/review-stack-in-coderabbit-ui.svg)](https://app.coderabbit.ai/change-stack/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/43?utm_source=github_walkthrough&utm_medium=github&utm_campaign=change_stack)\\n\\n<!-- review_stack_entry_end -->\\n\\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\",\"reactions\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/43/reactions\",\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"timeline_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/43/timeline\",\"performed_via_github_app\":null,\"state_reason\":null,\"score\":1},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/42\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/42/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/42/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/42/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/42\",\"id\":4459433744,\"node_id\":\"PR_kwDOSSFOvc7cMDW0\",\"number\":42,\"title\":\"feat(neverthrow): migrate packages to Result/ResultAsync pattern\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"lachiejames\",\"id\":47808687,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3ODA4Njg3\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47808687?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/lachiejames\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[],\"state\":\"closed\",\"locked\":false,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":2,\"created_at\":\"2026-05-16T09:35:12Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-16T19:25:08Z\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-05-16T19:25:06Z\",\"assignee\":null,\"author_association\":\"MEMBER\",\"type\":null,\"active_lock_reason\":null,\"draft\":false,\"pull_request\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/pulls/42\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/42\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/42.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/42.patch\",\"merged_at\":\"2026-05-16T19:25:06Z\"},\"body\":\"## Summary\\n\\nAdopts the [neverthrow](https://github.com/supermacro/neverthrow) Result/ResultAsync pattern across the SlopWeaver public repo, mirroring the established convention in `slopweaver-private`. Service code returns typed Result unions instead of throwing; boundary wrappers (`safeApiCall`, `safeQuery`) centralize exception-to-Result translation; per-package error unions discriminate on a `code` field; tests assert via strong `.isOk()`/`.isErr()` checks.\\n\\nCloses #41 (decision-record).\\n\\n**End-state:** `pnpm check:service-boundaries` reports **0 throws** in service-boundary files and is wired into `pnpm validate` as the first of 6 gates.\\n\\n## Convention waiver — please read first\\n\\nThis PR exceeds the repo's standard `≤500 LOC per PR` review-comfort ceiling. The maintainer accepted the waiver knowingly, per the migration plan and codex review (gpt-5.4) of the plan: a cross-cutting Result migration must move multiple packages together because the type signatures cascade (e.g. `upsertEvidence` changing return type forces `upsertSlackMessage` to change, which forces `pollMentions` to change, etc.). Splitting this across packages would leave each interim PR in a half-migrated state with inconsistent error shapes.\\n\\n**Reviewer guidance**: step through the 20 phase-aligned commits in order rather than reading the full diff. Each commit ends with `pnpm validate` green.\\n\\n## Why\\n\\n- Every error becomes part of a typed union; exhaustive `.match()` at boundaries replaces \\\"did I remember to catch this?\\\" review burden.\\n- Pre-alpha repo is the right time to set the convention — no deprecation runway.\\n- The private repo has converged on this pattern; aligning the public repo makes cross-repo code-sharing cheaper.\\n\\nCodex (gpt-5.4) reviewed the migration plan and surfaced 10 P0/P1 findings, all of which are incorporated. Notably: `@slopweaver/errors` is publishable (not `\\\"private\\\": true`); ESLint was wired into `pnpm validate` first (it was dormant before); `safeQuery` lives in `@slopweaver/db` while `DatabaseError` is shared via `@slopweaver/errors` so non-DB packages can include it in their unions without a DB dep; the CLI service-boundary check scope includes the cli-tools orchestration files (not just integrations).\\n\\n## What changed (by phase)\\n\\n**Phase 0** — `#41` decision-record filed.\\n\\n**Phase 1** — Foundation\\n- `52622fb` feat(errors): scaffold `@slopweaver/errors` (publishable; neverthrow@8.2.0 pinned exact)\\n- `7273393` chore(lint): wire ESLint into `pnpm lint` (it was dormant — only Biome ran)\\n- `639a283` docs(rules): `.claude/rules/error-handling.md` codifies the convention\\n\\n**Phase 2** — DB wrapper\\n- `414446c` feat(db): `safeQuery` + better-sqlite3 error-shape extractor\\n\\n**Phase 3** — Enforcement\\n- `8dd34a0` docs(eslint): `eslint-plugin-neverthrow@1.1.4` is incompatible with ESLint 10 (reads `context.parserServices` which moved in ESLint 9+); the rule is deferred until a maintained plugin lands or we ship a custom rule\\n- `948500f` feat(cli): `pnpm check:service-boundaries` scanner finds forbidden throws in service files\\n\\n**Phase 4** — Per-package migrations\\n- `21f791c` feat(env): `loadEnv` returns `Result<Env, EnvValidationError>`\\n- `768c6c4` feat(db): `integration-tokens` helpers return `ResultAsync` via `safeQuery`\\n- `5c35711` feat(integrations): core upsert helpers return `ResultAsync`\\n- `e6af23c` feat(slack): `SlackError` union; `createSlackClient` + `fetchIdentity` return Result\\n- `6ee5c43` feat(slack): `pollMentions` + `pollDMs` return Result; `MAX_PAGES` becomes `SLACK_PAGINATION_CAP_EXCEEDED`; `slackTsToIso` returns Result\\n- `ff1d51a` feat(github): `GithubError` union; `fetchIdentity` + pollers return Result; `safeGithubCall` extracts `RequestError.status`\\n- `6be9864` feat(mcp-server): tool handlers return Result; dispatcher emits `isError: true` structured response on Err\\n\\n**Phase 5** — cli-tools\\n- `97b27ea` feat(cli-tools): `worktree-new` returns `Result<…, WorktreeError>`; the homegrown `{ ok, error, exitCode }` discriminated union is replaced\\n- `86448c2` feat(cli-tools): `orchestration/core.ts` parsers return Result; introduces `OrchestrationErrors` factory + first three variants\\n- `111788d` feat(db,cli-tools): `resolveDataDir` / `resolveDbPath` return Result; both `@slopweaver/db` and the parallel `cli-tools/lib/data-dir.ts` helper share the `DATA_PATH_INVALID` discriminant; `createDb`/`checkDataDir` drop their default-param resolvers in favor of caller-side `.match()`\\n- `32ca716` feat(mcp-local): `validateToken` callback contract returns `ResultAsync<{ team }, BaseError>`; the temporary `throw new Error(slackResult.error.message)` rewrap at cli.ts:214 is removed; `@slopweaver/integrations-slack` barrel re-exports `safeSlackCall` + `SlackError` types\\n- `45d6a04` feat(cli-tools): runtime.ts end-to-end Result conversion — all 25 throws + the `lib/paths.ts` `findMonorepoRoot` throw (now visible to the wider scanner scope) become typed Result errors; new `OrchestrationError` union covers parser, state-precondition, retry-loop classifier (`ORCHESTRATION_MODEL_ATTEMPT { kind: 'transient'|'fatal' }`), all-models-failed, review/CI loop non-convergence, and subprocess wrappers; the 9 throwing methods on `RunOrchestrationEnvironment` change signature to return `Result<T, SubprocessFailedError>`; `prepareOrchestration`/`runOrchestration` return `Promise<Result<void, OrchestrationError | MonorepoRootNotFoundError>>`; cli.ts dispatcher drops the surrounding `try/catch` in favor of `.isErr()` + `process.exit(1)`\\n- `8d57a76` chore(validate): wire `pnpm check:service-boundaries` as the sixth gate (first in chain — cheapest, fastest feedback)\\n- `9f8880d` docs(rules): document throw carve-outs (browser fetchers, CLI entries, recovery catches) and the `eslint-plugin-neverthrow` deferral\\n\\n## Service-boundary throws\\n\\nPre-migration: ~30 throws across `integrations/*`, `mcp-server/tools/**`, `cli-tools/orchestration/{core,runtime}.ts`, `apps/mcp-local/src/connect/*`, plus `packages/db/src` and `packages/cli-tools/src/lib` once added to scope.\\n\\nPost-PR: **0 throws** at every configured service boundary. The scanner is now part of `pnpm validate`.\\n\\n## Test plan\\n\\n- [x] `pnpm validate` green on every commit (check:service-boundaries, format:check, lint, compile, test, knip — 6 gates)\\n- [x] Cassette tests for slack/github integrations replay unchanged (wire behavior preserved)\\n- [x] In-memory MCP `server.test.ts` round-trip works through new Result-aware dispatcher\\n- [x] `pnpm cli orchestration run @docs/orchestration/examples/refactor-example.md --dry-run` composes the phase plan correctly\\n- [x] `pnpm cli check-service-boundaries` reports 0 findings\\n- [ ] **Reviewer**: run `pnpm cli doctor` end-to-end (touches env, db, integrations indirectly)\\n- [ ] **Reviewer (optional)**: re-run a fresh codex review on commits 16-20 if a second opinion is wanted on the runtime.ts retry-loop conversion\\n\\n## Carve-outs (knowingly deferred)\\n\\n- **`eslint-plugin-neverthrow` runtime `must-use-result` rule** — upstream incompatible with ESLint 10. Documented in `eslint.config.js` and `.claude/rules/error-handling.md`. The CLI service-boundary scanner is the runtime enforcement until upstream catches up.\\n- **`packages/ui/src/client/api/diagnostics.ts:8`** — browser `fetch` throw, idiomatic for React Query / SWR / error-boundary patterns. Carve-out documented in `.claude/rules/error-handling.md`.\\n\\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\\n\\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\\n\\n* **New Features**\\n  * System-wide adoption of structured Result-style error handling and a new CLI check that scans service boundaries for unsafe throws.\\n\\n* **Bug Fixes**\\n  * CLI commands, integration connect flows, polling, DB operations, and server tool dispatch now surface failures consistently with proper exit codes and clearer error output.\\n\\n* **Documentation**\\n  * Added a comprehensive error-handling guide documenting conventions and allowed exceptions.\\n\\n* **Tests**\\n  * Expanded tests for Result consumption, error discriminants, and the service-boundary scanner.\\n\\n<!-- review_stack_entry_start -->\\n\\n[![Review Change Stack](https://storage.googleapis.com/coderabbit_public_assets/review-stack-in-coderabbit-ui.svg)](https://app.coderabbit.ai/change-stack/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/42?utm_source=github_walkthrough&utm_medium=github&utm_campaign=change_stack)\\n\\n<!-- review_stack_entry_end -->\\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\",\"reactions\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/42/reactions\",\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"timeline_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/42/timeline\",\"performed_via_github_app\":null,\"state_reason\":null,\"score\":1},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/40\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/40/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/40/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/40/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/40\",\"id\":4410399631,\"node_id\":\"PR_kwDOSSFOvc7ZvVXq\",\"number\":40,\"title\":\"docs(claude): add testing & code-quality rules and reviewer agents\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"lachiejames\",\"id\":47808687,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3ODA4Njg3\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47808687?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/lachiejames\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[],\"state\":\"closed\",\"locked\":false,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":2,\"created_at\":\"2026-05-09T01:01:45Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-16T15:45:23Z\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-05-16T15:45:22Z\",\"assignee\":null,\"author_association\":\"MEMBER\",\"type\":null,\"active_lock_reason\":null,\"draft\":false,\"pull_request\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/pulls/40\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/40\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/40.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/40.patch\",\"merged_at\":\"2026-05-16T15:45:22Z\"},\"body\":\"## What this PR does\\n\\nEstablishes the first wave of `.claude/rules/` and `.claude/agents/` content for this repo. Migrated and adapted from a sibling internal repo's testing-philosophy and code-quality material — the public's *current* shape, not the internal directory tiers.\\n\\n**Two new rule files**:\\n\\n- `.claude/rules/typescript-patterns.md` — named object params, TS1230 type-predicate exception, no `any`, `satisfies` over assertions, JSDoc on exported functions.\\n- `.claude/rules/testing.md` — test taxonomy (pure / Polly-replay / smoke), assertion *preferences* (not absolutist NEVERs), hard discipline rules, cassette-safety guidance pointing at `definePollySetup`'s redactor.\\n\\n**Four new sub-agents** under `.claude/agents/`:\\n\\n- `pure-function-test-reviewer` — pure-fn / DI-fake patterns; the cli-tools `core.ts` + effects shape; lists this repo's actual packages.\\n- `polly-replay-test-reviewer` — Polly cassette tests under `packages/integrations/*` (plain `*.test.ts`, not the aspirational `*.cassette.test.ts` suffix); recording-safety guidance.\\n- `frontend-pattern-reviewer` — React patterns + jsdom render-slice tests for `packages/ui/src/client/`; the `Diagnostics.test.tsx` shape.\\n- `docs-governance-reviewer` — CLAUDE.md / rules length and quality audits.\\n\\n**Two small edits**:\\n\\n- `.claude/rules/workflow.md` — append draft-PR-first habit, post-merge worktree cleanup commands, and a one-line cross-reference to `testing.md`.\\n- `CLAUDE.md` — single one-line cross-reference to `.claude/rules/{workflow, pr-conventions, testing, typescript-patterns}.md` so the rules are discoverable.\\n\\n## Why\\n\\nThe repo has had `.claude/commands/` and `.claude/rules/{workflow, pr-conventions}.md` for a while, but no testing-philosophy rule, no TypeScript conventions rule, and no sub-agents for repeating review tasks. Codifies the patterns that actually exist in the codebase today (DI fakes via `vi.fn`, Polly cassettes under `__recordings__/`, jsdom render slices with `vi.stubGlobal`) and sets a small forward-looking surface for the test culture to grow into.\\n\\nRefs #2 (v1.0.0 roadmap — quality bar).\\n\\n## Test plan\\n\\nPlan-driven verification (all green):\\n\\n- [x] `pnpm validate` — exit 0; format:check, lint, compile, test (19 cached), knip clean.\\n- [x] All `@.claude/...` cross-references resolve to real files.\\n- [x] No private-stack identifiers introduced by this branch (NestJS, Supabase, neverthrow, BullMQ, master-user, billing-profiles, etc.) — verified with branch-only diff grep.\\n- [x] All files under 200 lines (longest: `workflow.md` at 115 after edits).\\n- [x] All four sub-agent files have valid YAML frontmatter (`name`, `description`, `model`).\\n- [x] Existing tests using `vi.fn` / `expect(typeof…)` / `.toBeTruthy()` (~163 hits) are not outlawed — new rules are *preferences*, not absolutist NEVERs.\\n- [x] No vitest config references the aspirational `*.cassette.test.ts` / `*.smoke.test.ts` suffixes (so introducing them in docs only is correct).\\n- [x] All committed `.har` cassettes are token-free — only `Vary: Authorization, Cookie` response-cache header values matched the safety grep.\\n- [x] Existing pure-function test (`packages/cli-tools/src/doctor/checks.test.ts`) satisfies the new `pure-function-test-reviewer` rules.\\n\\n## Breaking changes\\n\\nNone.\\n\\n## Notes for the reviewer\\n\\n- The plan went through a `/codex` second-opinion review before implementation; codex's findings are folded in — see commit-history-adjacent plan file if curious.\\n- The assertion rules are deliberately soft (\\\"PREFER\\\", not \\\"NEVER\\\") because ~163 existing test sites use the older patterns. Tightening to absolutist NEVERs would create instant violations across `cli-tools`, `mcp-server`, `ui`, `slack`. New tests should still aim for the preferred shape.\\n- `.har` cassette redaction was verified end-to-end. The redactor in `packages/integrations/core/src/test-setup/polly.ts` is the single chokepoint; if a future cassette leaks, fix the redactor (don't just delete the cassette).\\n- `frontend-pattern-reviewer.md` is intentionally slim and forward-looking — `packages/ui/src/client/` is currently five files; the reviewer should grow with the surface, not pre-emptively enforce SPA-scale rules.\\n\\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\\n\\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\\n\\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\\n\\n* **Documentation**\\n  * Added agent guides for documentation governance review, frontend pattern auditing, Polly replay testing, and pure-function testing practices.\\n  * Established repository-wide testing rules including test taxonomy and cassette safety standards.\\n  * Documented TypeScript conventions for strict typing and naming patterns.\\n  * Updated workflow guidance with PR and post-merge cleanup procedures.\\n\\n<!-- review_stack_entry_start -->\\n\\n[![Review Change Stack](https://storage.googleapis.com/coderabbit_public_assets/review-stack-in-coderabbit-ui.svg)](https://app.coderabbit.ai/change-stack/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/40?utm_source=github_walkthrough&utm_medium=github&utm_campaign=change_stack)\\n\\n<!-- review_stack_entry_end -->\\n\\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\",\"reactions\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/40/reactions\",\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"timeline_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/40/timeline\",\"performed_via_github_app\":null,\"state_reason\":null,\"score\":1},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/34\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/34/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/34/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/34/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/34\",\"id\":4391818020,\"node_id\":\"PR_kwDOSSFOvc7Yye3w\",\"number\":34,\"title\":\"feat(mcp-local): slopweaver connect github + connect slack subcommands\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"lachiejames\",\"id\":47808687,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3ODA4Njg3\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47808687?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/lachiejames\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[],\"state\":\"closed\",\"locked\":false,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":2,\"created_at\":\"2026-05-06T13:42:12Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-08T11:49:55Z\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-05-08T11:49:52Z\",\"assignee\":null,\"author_association\":\"MEMBER\",\"type\":null,\"active_lock_reason\":null,\"draft\":false,\"pull_request\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/pulls/34\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/34\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/34.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/34.patch\",\"merged_at\":\"2026-05-08T11:49:52Z\"},\"body\":\"## What this PR does\\n\\nAdds two interactive subcommands to the published `slopweaver` binary:\\n\\n```bash\\nslopweaver connect github   # paste a fine-grained PAT\\nslopweaver connect slack    # paste a bot or user token (xoxb-/xoxp-)\\n```\\n\\nEach prompts for a token (input masked), validates it against the upstream API, and persists it into a new `integration_tokens` table in `@slopweaver/db`. A `loadIntegrationToken` helper exposes the stored value for the future polling layer / Wave 3 tools.\\n\\n## Why\\n\\nUntil this PR, end users had no way to give the GitHub/Slack polling integrations their tokens — `start_session` would have nothing to call once it lands. `refs #2` (v1.0.0 roadmap).\\n\\n## Design tradeoff: tokens-on-disk vs. table\\n\\nConsidered `~/.slopweaver/tokens.json` (mode 0600) vs. a new `integration_tokens` table.\\n\\n**Chose the table.** Reasoning:\\n\\n- The DB already exists and migrations run on every `createDb()`. Adding a small table is cheap.\\n- All other integration state (`integration_state`, `identity_graph`, `evidence_log`) lives in the same DB. A separate JSON file would create a second source of state with different ownership/locking semantics.\\n- Schema-tracked. Future encryption-at-rest, multi-account-per-integration, and rotation become migrations on a known shape rather than retroactively imposing schema on a JSON blob.\\n\\nThe migration was generated via `pnpm --filter @slopweaver/db drizzle-kit generate` from a clean `origin/main` baseline (single new `CREATE TABLE`).\\n\\n## Validation choice\\n\\n`connect` uses lightweight `users.getAuthenticated` / `auth.test` calls instead of the existing `fetchIdentity` helpers. `fetchIdentity` writes to `identity_graph` as a side effect; right for polling, wrong for `connect`, which should be re-runnable without leaving graph-state debris on a typo. The polling layer will reach for `loadIntegrationToken` → `fetchIdentity` later.\\n\\n## Test plan\\n\\n- [x] `pnpm validate` — all five gates green (format/lint/compile/test/knip)\\n- [x] New unit tests for `loadIntegrationToken` / `saveIntegrationToken` (4 tests; null lookup, scoped lookups, upsert, preserved `created_at_ms`)\\n- [x] New unit tests for `runConnectGithub` / `runConnectSlack` (7 tests; happy path, invalid token does NOT persist, repeat connect overwrites, Slack `team: null` fallback)\\n- [x] Existing `cli.smoke.test.ts` still passes (cac wiring preserves no-arg = MCP-stdio behavior)\\n- [x] Manual: `node apps/mcp-local/dist/cli.js --version` and `--help` both render correctly under cac\\n- [ ] Manual: paste a real PAT into `slopweaver connect github` (deferred; unit tests cover the logic)\\n\\n## Breaking changes\\n\\nNone — the no-subcommand default still launches the MCP server over stdio, and `--version` / `--help` still work (now via cac).\\n\\n## Out of scope (follow-ups)\\n\\nOAuth flows, token rotation, multi-account-per-integration, encryption at rest, `slopweaver disconnect`, `slopweaver status`.\\n\\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\\n\\n* **New Features**\\n  * Added a CLI \\\"connect\\\" command to link GitHub and Slack, validate tokens, and securely store credentials locally; CLI default now runs the local MCP server.\\n\\n* **Documentation**\\n  * README: new one-time setup section with commands to connect work tools and an optional PATH install note.\\n\\n* **Database**\\n  * Added persistent storage for integration tokens with timestamps and account/workspace labels.\\n\\n* **Tests**\\n  * New tests for connect flows, token validation, persistence/overwrite behavior, and a CLI smoke test.\\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\",\"reactions\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/34/reactions\",\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"timeline_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/34/timeline\",\"performed_via_github_app\":null,\"state_reason\":null,\"score\":1},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/36\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/36/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/36/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/36/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/36\",\"id\":4405887688,\"node_id\":\"PR_kwDOSSFOvc7ZgUZ5\",\"number\":36,\"title\":\"feat(ui): scaffold packages/ui + Diagnostics page on localhost:60701\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"lachiejames\",\"id\":47808687,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3ODA4Njg3\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47808687?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/lachiejames\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[],\"state\":\"closed\",\"locked\":false,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":4,\"created_at\":\"2026-05-08T11:06:19Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-08T11:49:25Z\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-05-08T11:40:33Z\",\"assignee\":null,\"author_association\":\"MEMBER\",\"type\":null,\"active_lock_reason\":null,\"draft\":false,\"pull_request\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/pulls/36\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/36\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/36.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/36.patch\",\"merged_at\":\"2026-05-08T11:40:33Z\"},\"body\":\"## What this PR does\\n\\nAdds `@slopweaver/web-ui` (the first React/Vite/browser-bundled package in the repo) and wires `apps/mcp-local` to serve its built static assets plus a tiny `GET /api/diagnostics` JSON endpoint on `127.0.0.1:60701`. Stdio MCP transport stays the primary surface; the web UI is opt-out via `--no-web-ui`.\\n\\nThe Diagnostics page surfaces:\\n- **Environment**: Node, pnpm, `~/.slopweaver/` (status badge per check, `>=22.12` floor)\\n- **Server**: bound host/port + listening flag\\n- **Integrations**: per-row `last_poll_started_at_ms` / `last_poll_completed_at_ms` + 10-min stale flag (read live from `integration_state` per request)\\n- **MCP clients**: count + transport (hardcoded `1 / stdio` until the SDK exposes connection lifecycle hooks — see follow-up)\\n\\n## Why\\n\\n`refs #2` (v1.0.0 roadmap). The roadmap lists this as the \\\"first-class onboarding UI\\\" — what a user sees if they hit `localhost:60701` right after `npm install -g @slopweaver/mcp-local`. Port 60701 was already pre-reserved as `LOCAL_API_PORT` in `pnpm cli doctor`'s preflight checks but nothing actually listened on it.\\n\\n## Architecture notes\\n\\n- **Two-output package**: `vite build` writes the React app to `packages/web-ui/dist/client/`; `tsc -p tsconfig.build.json` emits a Node-side server entry to `packages/web-ui/dist/server/`. The `main`/`exports` field points at `dist/server/index.js`. Splitting the tsconfig.build scope keeps DOM types out of the runtime entry that `apps/mcp-local` imports.\\n- **Boundary clean**: `packages/web-ui` is a `package`-element (consumed by `apps/mcp-local`, not the other way around per `eslint-plugin-boundaries` rules in `eslint.config.js`).\\n- **Doctor-check duplication**: the Node/pnpm/data-dir checks are intentional duplicates of a subset of `packages/cli-tools/src/doctor/checks.ts`. cli-tools is `private:true` with no build (`main: ./src/cli.ts`), so it can't be safely consumed by published runtime packages. The header comment in `packages/web-ui/src/server/checks.ts` documents the intentional severity divergence (web-ui softens pnpm failures from `fail` → `warn` since end users running the binary don't need pnpm).\\n- **`@types/node` bump**: `22.10.5` → `22.19.17` workspace-wide. Forced by Vite 8's peer dep `^20.19.0 || >=22.12.0`. Same iteration also raises `engines.node` and `.nvmrc` to `22.12.0+` so the doctor checks don't lie about supported Node versions.\\n- **Origin validation**: `/api/*` routes derive the allow-list from the live bound address (`{ host, port }`), so `SLOPWEAVER_WEB_UI_PORT=0` and ephemeral-port test scenarios work. IPv6 hosts are bracketed in URLs.\\n\\n## Out of scope (follow-ups to file)\\n\\n- `integration_state.last_error` column — the JSON reserves `lastError: null` so adding the column is non-breaking for the page.\\n- DNS-rebinding protection beyond Origin validation (host-header validation).\\n- Real MCP client connection counting (currently hardcoded `1`).\\n- Consolidating the doctor-check duplication once cli-tools is published or a runtime-safe `@slopweaver/diagnostics-core` exists.\\n\\n## Test plan\\n\\n- [x] Tests added / updated\\n- [x] Manually verified\\n- [ ] CI green\\n\\n**Automated** — `pnpm validate` (5 gates: format / lint / compile / test / knip) green:\\n- `packages/web-ui/src/server/checks.test.ts` — duplicated check fns, including minor-below-22.12 case.\\n- `packages/web-ui/src/server/diagnostics.test.ts` — response shape on empty DB, with rows, with stale rows. Always reports `lastError: null` in v1.\\n- `packages/web-ui/src/server/start.test.ts` — 11 cases: JSON shape, Origin matching/rejection (incl. bound-port and wrong-port), POST → 405, SPA fallback, asset MIME, `/../etc/passwd` doesn't leak files, port:0 reports actual bound port.\\n- `packages/web-ui/src/client/pages/Diagnostics.test.tsx` — 3 cases via @testing-library/react + jsdom: healthy / degraded / fetch-error.\\n- `apps/mcp-local/src/cli.smoke.test.ts` — spawns the compiled binary with `SLOPWEAVER_WEB_UI_PORT=0`, scrapes the bound URL from stderr, asserts `/api/diagnostics` JSON shape. Plus a deterministic `--no-web-ui` test that waits for an explicit \\\\\\\"web UI suppressed\\\\\\\" stderr line.\\n\\n**Manual** (verified locally):\\n- Booted the binary on `SLOPWEAVER_WEB_UI_PORT=60799`. `curl /api/diagnostics` returned the expected JSON. `GET /` served `index.html` (page title \\\\\\\"SlopWeaver — Diagnostics\\\\\\\"). `lsof` confirmed loopback-only bind (`localhost:60799`, not `*`). LAN-IP probe refused connection.\\n- Origin allow-list fix verified: `Origin: http://127.0.0.1:<bound>` → 200, `Origin: http://localhost:<bound>` → 200, `Origin: http://127.0.0.1:60701` (different port) → 403, `Origin: http://evil.example` → 403.\\n- `POST /api/diagnostics` → 405 with `Allow: GET, HEAD`.\\n\\n## Reviewed by codex\\n\\nThis branch went through the maintainer's hybrid Codex + Claude loop. Iteration 1 surfaced 2× P1 / 1× P2 / 2× Nit, addressed in the second commit; iteration 2 returned `REVIEW_STATUS: PASS`. Full transcripts will be posted as a single edited PR comment per the `/codex` flow.\\n\\n## Breaking changes\\n\\nNone for end users on Node 22.12+. Users on Node 22.0–22.11 will now get a clearer \\\\\\\"need >=22.12\\\\\\\" signal from the doctor and a `npm install` warning from `engines.node`. The published binary itself runs fine on 22.x; the dev toolchain (Vite 8) is the actual source of the floor.\\n\\n## Notes for the reviewer\\n\\n- The non-conflict touch-point with Terminal-2 (connect subcommands) is `apps/mcp-local/src/cli.ts`. My change adds `--no-web-ui` parsing + `startWebUiServer` lifecycle alongside any future `connect` subcommand block; whichever PR merges second resolves a trivial textual conflict.\\n- The `@types/node` bump is workspace-wide because pnpm hoists it; bumping only `packages/web-ui` would have caused version skew across packages. Same logic for `engines.node`.\\n\\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\\n\\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\\n\\n* **New Features**\\n  * Local Diagnostics web UI added (serves UI on loopback, default 127.0.0.1:60701)\\n  * Web UI shows environment checks, server & integration status, and MCP client summary\\n  * CLI: enable/disable web UI flag, support ephemeral port (0) and prints actual UI URL to stderr\\n\\n* **Behavior**\\n  * Web UI binds loopback-only and enforces Origin validation; port already-in-use is non-fatal (falls back)\\n\\n* **Documentation**\\n  * Node.js minimum requirement raised to >=22.12.0\\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\",\"reactions\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/36/reactions\",\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"timeline_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/36/timeline\",\"performed_via_github_app\":null,\"state_reason\":null,\"score\":1},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/35\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/35/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/35/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/35/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/35\",\"id\":4391836639,\"node_id\":\"PR_kwDOSSFOvc7Yyi4Z\",\"number\":35,\"title\":\"feat(mcp-server): implement start_session composite tool\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"lachiejames\",\"id\":47808687,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3ODA4Njg3\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47808687?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/lachiejames\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[],\"state\":\"closed\",\"locked\":false,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":2,\"created_at\":\"2026-05-06T13:44:43Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-08T11:08:48Z\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-05-08T11:06:57Z\",\"assignee\":null,\"author_association\":\"MEMBER\",\"type\":null,\"active_lock_reason\":null,\"draft\":false,\"pull_request\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/pulls/35\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/35\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/35.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/35.patch\",\"merged_at\":\"2026-05-08T11:06:57Z\"},\"body\":\"## What this PR does\\n\\nAdds the v1 flagship composite MCP tool. Reads ranked work-context evidence from `evidence_log` across the user's connected integrations, optionally triggering a fresh poll per integration when the cached state is stale or `force_refresh` is set. Wires the tool into `apps/mcp-local` so it's reachable end-to-end over stdio.\\n\\n## Why\\n\\n`start_session` is the demo that motivates the whole project — when a user opens Claude Code, it answers \\\"what should I work on next?\\\" by ranking recent evidence the local poller has captured. The wire contract was already locked in `@slopweaver/contracts`; both `@slopweaver/integrations-github` and `@slopweaver/integrations-slack` are merged with poll exports; this PR fills the last big gap.\\n\\nrefs #2\\n\\n## Design notes\\n\\n- **Pollers are injected via factory args**, not read from `ToolHandlerContext`. The MCP context deliberately does not carry auth tokens; the host (`apps/mcp-local`) builds closures that capture tokens at startup. Tests pass `vi.fn()` mocks.\\n- **Stale threshold** is a top-of-file constant (`DEFAULT_STALE_THRESHOLD_MS = 10 * 60 * 1000`), overridable via factory arg for tests.\\n- **Ranking heuristic** is intentionally simple, documented in a top-of-file comment so the formula is easy to swap later: `score = recencyScore + kindBoost`, where `recencyScore = 1 / (1 + ageHours / 24)` and `kindBoost = 0.5` for `kind ∈ {mention, review_request, dm}`.\\n- **v1 wires no pollers into `apps/mcp-local`**: integration auth-token plumbing is a separate concern. `force_refresh` is a no-op until tokens land; cached evidence and freshness reports still work correctly.\\n\\n## Test plan\\n\\n- [x] 8 unit tests in `packages/mcp-server/src/tools/composite/start-session.test.ts` (happy path with kind boost, empty DB, integrations filter, max_items cap + schema rejection, force_refresh poller dispatch, stale auto-poll + threshold respect, missing-state-row freshness, citation_url → ref discriminated union)\\n- [x] 1 server-level integration test in `server.test.ts` (registers tool over `InMemoryTransport`, asserts `StartSessionResult.safeParse` succeeds)\\n- [x] 1 smoke assertion in `apps/mcp-local/src/cli.smoke.test.ts` (advertises `start_session` over stdio + returns valid empty `StartSessionResult` against a fresh tmp DB)\\n- [x] `pnpm validate` green (format:check, lint, compile, test, knip)\\n\\n## Breaking changes\\n\\nNone.\\n\\n## Notes for the reviewer\\n\\n- Out of scope (separate Wave 3 PRs): `get_context_on`, `get_pr_context`, `catch_me_up`, `search_work_context`, `get_freshness`.\\n- Added `drizzle-orm` as a direct dependency of `@slopweaver/mcp-server` (was previously transitive via `@slopweaver/db`); the tool's handler uses `eq`, `inArray`, `desc` directly.\\n- `humanAge()` produces locale-independent strings (`5m ago`, `2h ago`, `3d ago`) deliberately — `Intl.RelativeTimeFormat` would couple test assertions to system locale.\\n\\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\\n\\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\\n\\n* **New Features**\\n  * Added `start_session` tool that retrieves and intelligently ranks work items based on activity and evidence from integrated sources\\n  * Features automatic cache refresh with configurable staleness detection to keep recommendations current\\n  * Gracefully handles incomplete or malformed source data without interrupting service\\n\\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\",\"reactions\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/35/reactions\",\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"timeline_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/35/timeline\",\"performed_via_github_app\":null,\"state_reason\":null,\"score\":1},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/31\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/31/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/31/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/31/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/31\",\"id\":4390332955,\"node_id\":\"PR_kwDOSSFOvc7YtkSu\",\"number\":31,\"title\":\"feat(integrations): packages/integrations/slack polling for mentions/DMs\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"lachiejames\",\"id\":47808687,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3ODA4Njg3\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47808687?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/lachiejames\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[],\"state\":\"closed\",\"locked\":false,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":3,\"created_at\":\"2026-05-06T09:43:30Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-06T13:25:21Z\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-05-06T13:25:18Z\",\"assignee\":null,\"author_association\":\"MEMBER\",\"type\":null,\"active_lock_reason\":null,\"draft\":false,\"pull_request\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/pulls/31\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/31\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/31.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/31.patch\",\"merged_at\":\"2026-05-06T13:25:18Z\"},\"body\":\"## What this PR does\\n\\nScaffolds `@slopweaver/integrations-slack` — the first package under `packages/integrations/`. Exports four entrypoints:\\n\\n- `pollMentions({ db, token, since? })` — `auth.test` + `search.messages` against `<@U…>`; upserts `evidence_log` with `kind='mention'`.\\n- `pollDMs({ db, token, since? })` — `conversations.list?types=im` then `conversations.history` per IM channel; upserts `evidence_log` with `kind='message'`.\\n- `fetchIdentity({ db, token })` — `auth.test` + `users.info`; upserts `identity_graph` preserving `canonical_id` and `created_at_ms` across re-runs.\\n- `createSlackClient({ token, fetch?, sleep? })` — fetch wrapper that honours 429 `Retry-After` once before surfacing a `SlackApiError`.\\n\\n## Why\\n\\n`refs #2` (v1.0.0 roadmap). One of the three Terminal 3 scaffolding worktrees. Establishes the integration-package shape that github / linear / jira will mirror in follow-up PRs.\\n\\n## How HTTP testing is wired\\n\\nAdopts the Polly + nock cassette stack used in `slopweaver-private`:\\n\\n- `@pollyjs/{core,adapter-node-http,persister-fs}@6.0.6` + `nock@13.5.6` (root `pnpm.overrides` pins nock for adapter compatibility).\\n- `patches/@pollyjs__adapter-node-http@6.0.6.patch` (copied verbatim from the private repo) fixes HTTPS request handling and content-encoding edge cases.\\n- `node-fetch@3.3.2` replaces `globalThis.fetch` in `src/test/setup-polly.ts` so requests go through Node's `http` module where Polly can intercept (Node 22's native undici-based fetch bypasses Polly's adapter otherwise).\\n- `setup-polly.ts` is loaded as a vitest `setupFile`; it scrubs auth headers and token-shaped JSON values before persisting cassettes.\\n\\nThe initial scaffold tests inject a fake `SlackClient` via DI rather than using cassettes, since no real Slack workspace is available to record against. The Polly infrastructure is wired and ready — see README for the `POLLY_MODE=record SLACK_BOT_TOKEN=…` re-record flow when a workspace is connected.\\n\\n## Pre-requisite config changes\\n\\n- `pnpm-workspace.yaml`: added `packages/integrations/*` so nested packages register as workspaces.\\n- `eslint.config.js`: added `{ type: 'package', pattern: 'packages/integrations/*' }` to `boundaries/elements` so imports inside the slack package satisfy `boundaries/element-types`.\\n\\n## Out of scope\\n\\n- OAuth installation flow / token storage\\n- Write operations (sending messages, reactions)\\n- Threads (`thread_ts`)\\n- RTM / Socket Mode / Events API webhooks\\n- Slash commands\\n- Wiring this package into `mcp-server` tools\\n- Reconciliation of github vs slack package shape (deferred until both exist)\\n\\n## Test plan\\n\\n- [x] `pnpm format:check` ✅\\n- [x] `pnpm lint` ✅\\n- [x] `pnpm compile` ✅\\n- [x] `pnpm test` — 16 new tests pass; full repo suite stays green ✅\\n- [x] `pnpm knip` ✅\\n- [ ] Re-record cassettes against a real Slack bot token (follow-up PR once a workspace is connected)\\n\\n## Notes for the reviewer\\n\\n- Tests use injected fake `SlackClient` rather than Polly cassettes for now — the Polly infrastructure is ready for first-record but not yet exercised end-to-end. Worth deciding whether to keep cassettes per-developer or commit them (root `.gitignore` excludes `*.har` as a safety net; README flags the trade-off).\\n- `client.ts` and the Slack permalink derivation in `mentions.ts` are tested directly; the `auth.test` + `users.info` two-step in `fetchIdentity` reflects the bot-token reality (`users.identity` requires a user-token scope).\\n- One worktree = one branch = one PR — this is one of three Terminal 3 worktrees in flight; `pnpm-workspace.yaml` and `eslint.config.js` edits may conflict with sibling PRs touching the same files.\\n\\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\\n\\n* **New Features**\\n  * Added a Slack integration package exposing client creation and APIs to poll mentions, DMs, and fetch identity.\\n\\n* **Tests**\\n  * Added comprehensive tests, HTTP recording/replay support, in-memory test DB helpers, and a Vitest test setup.\\n\\n* **Documentation**\\n  * Reworked Slack integration README with API, testing, and development guidance.\\n\\n* **Chores**\\n  * Updated workspace, lint boundaries, build/test configs, package manager settings, and added a runtime/patch for HTTP adapter.\\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\",\"reactions\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/31/reactions\",\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"timeline_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/31/timeline\",\"performed_via_github_app\":null,\"state_reason\":null,\"score\":1},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/33\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/33/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/33/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/33/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/33\",\"id\":4390745226,\"node_id\":\"PR_kwDOSSFOvc7Yu7Ew\",\"number\":33,\"title\":\"feat(integrations): packages/integrations/github polling for PRs/issues/mentions\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"lachiejames\",\"id\":47808687,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3ODA4Njg3\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47808687?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/lachiejames\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[],\"state\":\"closed\",\"locked\":false,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":2,\"created_at\":\"2026-05-06T10:51:51Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-06T11:45:45Z\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-05-06T11:44:48Z\",\"assignee\":null,\"author_association\":\"MEMBER\",\"type\":null,\"active_lock_reason\":null,\"draft\":false,\"pull_request\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/pulls/33\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/33\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/33.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/33.patch\",\"merged_at\":\"2026-05-06T11:44:48Z\"},\"body\":\"## What this PR does\\n\\nScaffolds `@slopweaver/integrations-github` — the first concrete writer for `evidence_log` and `identity_graph`. Public surface:\\n\\n- `pollPullRequests({ db, token, since })` / `pollIssues(...)` — search-based pollers that upsert each result into `evidence_log` (kind-prefixed `external_id`: `pr_<id>` / `issue_<id>` / `mention_<id>` so a same-id mention can't collide with the underlying PR/issue).\\n- `pollMentions({ db, token, since, username })` — explicit username because GitHub's `mentions:` qualifier rejects `@me`. v1 ships PR mentions only (`/search/issues` now requires `is:pr` or `is:issue`); issue mentions follow up.\\n- `fetchIdentity({ db, token })` — `GET /user` then upsert into `identity_graph`. v1 `canonical_id` is the sentinel `github:<external_id>`.\\n- `githubFetch({ token, path, … })` — minimal REST wrapper. Reads `X-RateLimit-Remaining`/`Reset` and sleeps until reset when remaining < threshold (default 10). Sleep is injectable.\\n\\nAll upserts use Drizzle `onConflictDoUpdate` against the existing `(integration, external_id)` UNIQUE constraints. `integration_state.cursor` advances to the latest `updated_at` on success; `last_poll_started_at_ms` / `last_poll_completed_at_ms` diverge only if a poll fails midway.\\n\\n## Why\\n\\n`evidence_log` and `identity_graph` have been waiting for a writer. This is the proving ground for the polling + upsert pattern future integrations (Slack, Linear) will follow.\\n\\n`refs #2`\\n\\n## Test plan\\n\\n- [x] `pnpm format:check` ✅\\n- [x] `pnpm lint` ✅\\n- [x] `pnpm compile` ✅\\n- [x] `pnpm test` ✅ (16/16 in replay mode, no token needed)\\n- [x] `pnpm knip` ✅\\n- [x] Polly cassettes recorded against a fine-grained PAT (public_repo + read:user) and inspected line-by-line before commit\\n- [x] `git grep -E 'gh[posu]_[A-Za-z0-9]{16,}' packages/integrations/github/` — clean\\n- [x] All search/issues queries scoped to `repo:slopweaver/slopweaver` at record time\\n- [x] `/user` response 100% placeholdered (login=test-user, id=1, etc.)\\n\\n## Polly + nock + node-fetch test infrastructure\\n\\nPulled in:\\n- `@pollyjs/{core,adapter-node-http,persister-fs}@6.0.6`\\n- `nock@13.5.6` (pinned via `pnpm.overrides` — Polly's adapter requires this exact version)\\n- `node-fetch@3.3.2` (native fetch / undici bypasses Polly's node-http adapter; the setup file replaces `globalThis.fetch` with node-fetch for tests, restored in `afterAll`)\\n- `patches/@pollyjs__adapter-node-http@6.0.6.patch` (verbatim from the SaaS repo) wired through `pnpm.patchedDependencies` — fixes HTTPS handling in the upstream adapter\\n\\nSetup file: `packages/integrations/github/src/test-setup/polly.ts`. Each test gets its own cassette under `<test-file-dir>/__recordings__/<suite>/<test>/recording.har`. Replay (default, CI) is missing-cassette-fails-loudly; record (`POLLY_MODE=record` + `GH_TOKEN`) is local-only.\\n\\n## Three layers of cassette-leak defence\\n\\nFor a public-repo cassette to be safe, every layer below has to hold:\\n\\n1. **Scope-limited PAT.** Fine-grained, public_repo + read:user only. Even an unscoped `involves:@me` query can't return private-repo data.\\n2. **Search-query scope rewrite at record time.** Polly request hook adds `repo:slopweaver/slopweaver` to outgoing `/search/issues` queries. Replay matcher ignores query params, so production code's unscoped queries still match.\\n3. **`beforePersist` content redaction.** `/user` response fields → stable placeholders. `Authorization` / `Cookie` / `Set-Cookie` / `X-GitHub-Request-Id` / `github-authentication-token-expiration` headers stripped. PAT-shaped strings → `[REDACTED-PAT]`.\\n\\nSee `packages/integrations/github/README.md` for the recording flow.\\n\\n## Out of scope (file as follow-up issues)\\n\\n- OAuth / GitHub App installation (today: PAT only)\\n- Webhooks (push-based deltas)\\n- GraphQL endpoints (REST is enough for v1)\\n- Comment-level mentions (`/notifications` endpoint)\\n- Issue mentions (v1 mentions poll is `is:pr mentions:<user>` only)\\n- Pagination beyond `per_page=50`\\n- Write operations (creating PRs/issues/comments)\\n\\n## Notes for the reviewer\\n\\n- `external_id` for evidence rows is kind-prefixed (`pr_`, `issue_`, `mention_`) so a same-id mention row can't collide with the underlying PR/issue\\n- `canonical_id` for v1 is `github:<external_id>` (placeholder until multi-integration merge UI lands)\\n- Cassettes recorded once locally with a fine-grained PAT; CI never makes live calls\\n- ~90% of cassette byte volume is real public slopweaver/slopweaver data (anyone can pull the same via `gh api`); ~10% is placeholder `/user` profiles\\n\\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\\n\\n* **New Features**\\n  * Released a GitHub integration package: authenticated client, identity fetch, and pollers for PRs, issues, and mentions.\\n\\n* **Tests**\\n  * Added comprehensive tests with recorded HTTP interactions and a test setup for reliable replay/record workflows.\\n\\n* **Documentation**\\n  * Added package README documenting public APIs and testing guidance.\\n\\n* **Chores**\\n  * Enabled tracking of test recordings and updated workspace/package tooling and patches for test/runtime stability.\\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\",\"reactions\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/33/reactions\",\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"timeline_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/33/timeline\",\"performed_via_github_app\":null,\"state_reason\":null,\"score\":1},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/30\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/30/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/30/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/30/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/30\",\"id\":4390272840,\"node_id\":\"PR_kwDOSSFOvc7YtXet\",\"number\":30,\"title\":\"feat(env): scaffold @slopweaver/env with Zod env-var validation\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"lachiejames\",\"id\":47808687,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3ODA4Njg3\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47808687?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/lachiejames\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[],\"state\":\"closed\",\"locked\":false,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":2,\"created_at\":\"2026-05-06T09:34:20Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-06T10:54:23Z\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-05-06T10:54:21Z\",\"assignee\":null,\"author_association\":\"MEMBER\",\"type\":null,\"active_lock_reason\":null,\"draft\":false,\"pull_request\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/pulls/30\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/30\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/30.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/30.patch\",\"merged_at\":\"2026-05-06T10:54:21Z\"},\"body\":\"## What this PR does\\n\\nAdds a new `@slopweaver/env` workspace package: a Zod schema for the binary's\\nenv-var surface (`XDG_DATA_HOME`, `NODE_ENV`, `LOG_LEVEL`) plus a `loadEnv()`\\nhelper that parses, freezes, and returns the result. On invalid input it\\nthrows a single `EnvValidationError` with the **full** list of issues —\\nnever fail-fast on the first. Wired into `apps/mcp-local/src/cli.ts` as a\\nstartup-time validation call (after `--version`/`--help` short-circuits,\\nbefore `createDb`).\\n\\n## Why\\n\\nPre-empts the env contract before v1 OAuth callbacks, the localhost web UI\\nport, and structured logging land. Gives the binary a single fail-fast\\nboundary for malformed env. refs #2.\\n\\n## Test plan\\n\\n- [x] `pnpm validate` (format / lint / compile / test / knip) green\\n- [x] `packages/env/src/index.test.ts` covers: happy path, defaults,\\n      optional `XDG_DATA_HOME` omitted, multi-error aggregation, frozen\\n      result (5 vitest blocks)\\n- [x] `apps/mcp-local/src/cli.smoke.test.ts` still green — the new\\n      `loadEnv()` call doesn't regress the MCP boot path\\n\\n## Breaking changes\\n\\nNone.\\n\\n## Notes for the reviewer\\n\\n- `packages/db/src/path.ts` keeps reading `process.env.XDG_DATA_HOME`\\n  directly. The \\\"no `process.env` outside `@slopweaver/env`\\\" rule applies to\\n  apps, not packages — db's resolver remains testable via its named-param\\n  override.\\n- The `loadEnv()` result is intentionally discarded by `cli.ts` for now;\\n  future tools that need `NODE_ENV` / `LOG_LEVEL` will consume the same\\n  `loadEnv()` API. The call exists today purely for fail-fast validation.\\n- Schema is **not** `.strict()` — `process.env` contains many unrelated\\n  keys (`PATH`, `HOME`, …) and Zod's default `strip` mode discards them.\\n\\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\\n\\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\\n\\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\\n\\n## Release Notes\\n\\n* **New Features**\\n  * Added environment variable validation with detailed error reporting at startup.\\n\\n* **Bug Fixes**\\n  * Enhanced error handling during application initialization with improved failure messages.\\n\\n* **Documentation**\\n  * Updated guidance on environment configuration, emphasizing that XDG_DATA_HOME must be an absolute path.\\n\\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\",\"reactions\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/30/reactions\",\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"timeline_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/30/timeline\",\"performed_via_github_app\":null,\"state_reason\":null,\"score\":1},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/32\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/32/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/32/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/32/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/32\",\"id\":4390678997,\"node_id\":\"PR_kwDOSSFOvc7YutC2\",\"number\":32,\"title\":\"chore(security): wire gitleaks via lefthook + CI gate\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"lachiejames\",\"id\":47808687,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3ODA4Njg3\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47808687?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/lachiejames\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[],\"state\":\"closed\",\"locked\":false,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":2,\"created_at\":\"2026-05-06T10:40:05Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-06T10:49:31Z\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-05-06T10:49:24Z\",\"assignee\":null,\"author_association\":\"MEMBER\",\"type\":null,\"active_lock_reason\":null,\"draft\":false,\"pull_request\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/pulls/32\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/32\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/32.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/32.patch\",\"merged_at\":\"2026-05-06T10:49:24Z\"},\"body\":\"## What this PR does\\n\\nAdds layered secret scanning to this public repo so contributors (including AI agents) can't accidentally land tokens, keys, or other credentials.\\n\\nThe model is three layers of defence:\\n\\n1. **Local pre-commit hook** — `lefthook` runs `gitleaks protect --staged` on staged content. Fast feedback before the commit lands.\\n2. **CI gate** — sixth gate in `.github/workflows/ci.yml`. Installs `gitleaks v8.30.1` from the official SHA-pinned tarball, then runs `gitleaks detect --no-git --source .` over the full tree. Catches anything that bypassed the hook (e.g. `git commit --no-verify`).\\n3. **Maintainer review** — already in place; this PR moves the maintainer off the critical path.\\n\\nThe pre-push hook listed in the chain's \\\"in scope\\\" section was deferred via the tightening prompt — it largely duplicates the CI gate while adding latency on every push and edge cases around push destinations. CI is the backstop. If we hit a real case where it would help, we can add it as a follow-up.\\n\\n## Why\\n\\n`refs #2` — this is one of the v1.0.0 hardening items. The repo is public and the only thing currently keeping a secret out of `main` is the maintainer's eyes. That's a single-point-of-failure, especially when AI agents are driving commits.\\n\\n## What changed\\n\\n- `lefthook` added as a root devDependency (pinned to `2.1.6` to match repo style)\\n- New `prepare` root script: `lefthook install || echo 'lefthook install skipped (not a git repository)'` — tolerates non-git checkouts (tarball / sandbox)\\n- New `lefthook.yml` with one `pre-commit` job that fails loudly if `gitleaks` is missing from PATH\\n- New `.gitleaks.toml` extending the default rule pack with one narrow allowlist: the fake `xoxb-…-test-secret-DELETE` literal documented in `.claude/orchestration/security/gitleaks-secret-scanning.md` (the chain doc this PR was built from)\\n- `.github/workflows/ci.yml` adds two steps after `pnpm test`: install gitleaks via SHA-verified tarball, then run the scan\\n- `CONTRIBUTING.md` adds three short paragraphs: install, what to do if the hook fires, `--no-verify` policy\\n- `.claude/rules/workflow.md` adds a one-paragraph note pointing at CONTRIBUTING.md\\n\\n## Test plan\\n\\n- [x] Planted a fake `xoxb-…-deadbeef…` token in a scratch file, attempted `git commit`, confirmed the lefthook pre-commit hook blocked the commit. Removed the file.\\n- [x] Ran `gitleaks detect --no-git --source . --config .gitleaks.toml` against the full tree → `no leaks found` (the chain doc's documented fake token is allowlisted by path + regex).\\n- [x] All five existing CI gates pass locally: `pnpm format:check && pnpm lint && pnpm compile && pnpm test && pnpm knip`.\\n- [x] `pnpm install` triggered the `prepare` script which ran `lefthook install` and synced the pre-commit hook.\\n- [ ] CI passes on this PR (will verify after push).\\n- [ ] Maintainer manual QA: plant a different fake secret locally, attempt commit, confirm hook fires.\\n\\n## Notes for reviewer\\n\\n- **Why not `gitleaks-action`?** The official GitHub Action requires `GITLEAKS_LICENSE` for org-owned repos. We don't want CI to depend on a paid secret. Installing the binary directly via SHA-pinned tarball is license-free, deterministic, and matches the repo's \\\"pin every action by full SHA\\\" convention.\\n- **Why is the allowlist global (`[allowlist]`) and not per-rule (`[[allowlists]]`)?** The plural `[[allowlists]]` syntax did not match correctly on locally-installed `gitleaks 8.22.1`; the global `[allowlist]` form works on both 8.22.1 and 8.30.1 and is the minimum viable shape. We can revisit if we add more allowlist entries.\\n- **Version skew:** local install instructions and CI are both pinned to `v8.30.1`. Contributors with older binaries should still work for staged-content scans, but there's a documented version target so we can deprecate older versions later if rule changes matter.\\n\\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\\n\\n* **Documentation**\\n  * Added contributor guidance for secret scanning, local setup instructions, and guidance for handling findings.\\n\\n* **Chores**\\n  * Enabled repository secret scanning in CI.\\n  * Added pre-commit hooks to detect secrets locally and require installation of the scanner.\\n  * Require disclosure in PRs if hooks are bypassed.\\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\",\"reactions\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/32/reactions\",\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"timeline_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/32/timeline\",\"performed_via_github_app\":null,\"state_reason\":null,\"score\":1},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/29\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/29/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/29/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/29/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/29\",\"id\":4371750492,\"node_id\":\"PR_kwDOSSFOvc7XxQtG\",\"number\":29,\"title\":\"docs: add docs/CODEBASE_MAP.md + enable cartographer plugin\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"lachiejames\",\"id\":47808687,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3ODA4Njg3\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47808687?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/lachiejames\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[],\"state\":\"closed\",\"locked\":false,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":1,\"created_at\":\"2026-05-03T12:10:42Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-03T13:01:34Z\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-05-03T13:01:33Z\",\"assignee\":null,\"author_association\":\"MEMBER\",\"type\":null,\"active_lock_reason\":null,\"draft\":false,\"pull_request\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/pulls/29\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/29\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/29.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/29.patch\",\"merged_at\":\"2026-05-03T13:01:33Z\"},\"body\":\"## What this PR does\\n\\nAdds `docs/CODEBASE_MAP.md` — the architecture map that the codex orchestration runner auto-injects as a prompt prefix (`codex-agent --map`) — and wires up the [Cartographer](https://github.com/kingbootoshi/cartographer) plugin used to generate it.\\n\\n## Why\\n\\nThe runner already passes `--map` and falls back gracefully when no map exists, but for non-trivial chains it leaves codex without project context. With the map present, planners and reviewers start with the same shared view of the repo: the four current packages (`cli-tools`, `contracts`, `db`, `mcp-server`), the eventual `apps/mcp-local` composition, the 5 CI gates, and the conventions a newcomer would otherwise have to grep for.\\n\\n## What's in the map\\n\\n- System overview Mermaid diagram (current packages + future apps)\\n- Per-package module guide with public surfaces, schemas, and table list\\n- Three sequence diagrams: worktree creation, MCP request flow, full `/codex` orchestration loop\\n- Stack, CI gates, conventions\\n- Gotchas surfaced from the source (e.g. migrations folder resolved via `import.meta.url` not cwd; `--executor hybrid` silently overridden on `run`; review-pass sentinel exact strings; `MAX_REVIEW_ATTEMPTS = 5`)\\n- Navigation guide for common tasks (add MCP tool, add DB table, add doctor check, add CLI subcommand, add orchestration phase, change CI gates)\\n\\n## Test plan\\n\\n- [x] `pnpm validate` (format:check + lint + compile + test + knip) — all 5 gates pass locally\\n- [x] `docs/CODEBASE_MAP.md` accurately reflects the four current packages (verified against source via 3 parallel Sonnet subagents reading 93 files)\\n- [x] `CLAUDE.md` overview is concise and points at the map\\n- [x] `.claude/settings.json` plugin entry uses the documented form `cartographer@cartographer-marketplace`\\n- [x] Mermaid diagrams render in GitHub's markdown preview\\n\\n## Breaking changes\\n\\nNone.\\n\\n## Notes for the reviewer\\n\\n- The map is checked in deliberately (per the new `docs/contributing/ai-workflow.md` section): treat it as documentation, review the diff before refresh-commits, and avoid pasting in private-repo content.\\n- The four pre-existing modifications on this branch (`.claude/settings.json`, `docs/contributing/ai-workflow.md`, `docs/orchestration/chain-format.md`, plus the new `CLAUDE.md` overview) are all cartographer setup — keeping them in one PR matches the branch slug `add-codebase-map`.\\n- Future refresh runs (`/cartographer` again) only re-analyze changed modules per the plugin's diff-aware update mode.\\n\\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\\n\\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\\n\\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\\n\\n* **Documentation**\\n  * Added comprehensive codebase map documenting repository structure, architecture, module organization, and technology stack.\\n  * Enhanced developer documentation with AI-assisted workflow guidance and codebase navigation instructions.\\n  * Updated orchestration documentation with automatic codebase context injection details.\\n\\n* **Chores**\\n  * Enabled Cartographer plugin for enhanced AI code analysis capabilities.\\n\\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\",\"reactions\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/29/reactions\",\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"timeline_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/29/timeline\",\"performed_via_github_app\":null,\"state_reason\":null,\"score\":1},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/28\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/28/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/28/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/28/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/28\",\"id\":4371623066,\"node_id\":\"PR_kwDOSSFOvc7Xw2xm\",\"number\":28,\"title\":\"feat(mcp-local): scaffold @slopweaver/mcp-local — publishable stdio MCP binary\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"lachiejames\",\"id\":47808687,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3ODA4Njg3\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47808687?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/lachiejames\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[],\"state\":\"closed\",\"locked\":false,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":1,\"created_at\":\"2026-05-03T11:25:30Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-03T12:59:54Z\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-05-03T12:59:07Z\",\"assignee\":null,\"author_association\":\"MEMBER\",\"type\":null,\"active_lock_reason\":null,\"draft\":false,\"pull_request\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/pulls/28\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/28\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/28.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/28.patch\",\"merged_at\":\"2026-05-03T12:59:07Z\"},\"body\":\"## What this PR does\\n\\nScaffolds `apps/mcp-local/` — the v1 CLI binary. It wires\\n`@slopweaver/db` and `@slopweaver/mcp-server` together and exposes the\\n`slopweaver` command, which runs an MCP server over stdio. After this\\nlands, the published install snippet works:\\n\\n```bash\\nclaude mcp add slopweaver -- npx -y @slopweaver/mcp-local\\n```\\n\\n## Why\\n\\ncloses #22 — the v1 MVP milestone. With this app in place, Claude Code,\\nCursor, Cline, and Codex CLI can all talk to a SlopWeaver server with\\nzero auth dance, per decision #11 (stdio-only). Sequential consumer of\\n#19 / #20 / #21.\\n\\n## What's in the app\\n\\n- **`src/cli.ts`** — entry. Parses `--version` / `-v` and `--help` / `-h`\\n  (writes to stdout, exits). Default behavior opens the SQLite DB at\\n  `resolveDbPath()` (honours `XDG_DATA_HOME`), registers the `ping`\\n  builtin from `@slopweaver/mcp-server`, calls `startStdio({ server })`.\\n  SIGINT/SIGTERM gracefully close the MCP server and the DB handle so\\n  the SQLite file lock is released cleanly.\\n- **`build.mjs`** — esbuild bundler. ESM, target node22, single output\\n  at `dist/cli.js` with a `#!/usr/bin/env node` shebang. `better-sqlite3`\\n  is marked `external` (native module; can't be bundled). Banner injects\\n  a `createRequire` shim because `drizzle-orm/better-sqlite3` reaches for\\n  CJS internally. Copies `packages/db/migrations/` to `./migrations/` so\\n  the runtime `migrate(db, { migrationsFolder })` resolves correctly\\n  relative to the bundled `import.meta.url`. `chmod 0o755` on the output\\n  so the `bin` is executable. Version is injected via\\n  `esbuild --define` from `package.json#version`.\\n- **`src/cli.smoke.test.ts`** — end-to-end test. Spawns the built\\n  `dist/cli.js` via `StdioClientTransport` (real `child_process.spawn`),\\n  points `XDG_DATA_HOME` at a per-test tmp dir so the SQLite file never\\n  hits the developer's real `~/.slopweaver/`, sends a `tools/list`,\\n  asserts `ping` is advertised, and round-trips a `tools/call ping`\\n  whose `structuredContent` validates against the `PingResult`\\n  contract. Also asserts the executable bit on `dist/cli.js`.\\n- **`turbo.json` local override** — `test` depends on `build` so the\\n  smoke test always runs against a fresh bundle (the root `turbo.json`\\n  only does `^build`, which doesn't cover the current package).\\n- **`apps/mcp-local/.gitignore`** — `migrations/` is a build artefact\\n  (copy of `packages/db/migrations`, the single source of truth). The\\n  published tarball ships them via `package.json#files`, but git never\\n  tracks them.\\n- **Root `knip.json`** — `apps/mcp-local` ignores `better-sqlite3` +\\n  `@types/better-sqlite3` since they're external runtime resolutions,\\n  not direct source imports.\\n\\n## Test plan\\n\\nRun from this branch:\\n\\n- [x] `pnpm format:check` — green\\n- [x] `pnpm lint` — green (no new findings; pre-existing infos in\\n  `packages/cli-tools/orchestration/*` only)\\n- [x] `pnpm compile` — green (5 packages, including the new app)\\n- [x] `pnpm test` — green (2 new tests: the executable-bit assertion\\n  and the stdio `tools/list` + `tools/call` round-trip)\\n- [x] `pnpm knip` — green\\n- [x] Manual smoke: `dist/cli.js --version` prints `0.0.0`;\\n  `dist/cli.js --help` prints the wire-into-Claude-Code snippet.\\n\\n`pnpm validate` runs all five gates and is also green.\\n\\n## Breaking changes\\n\\nNone. New app; no existing consumers.\\n\\n## Notes for the reviewer\\n\\n- **Bundling vs separate-package install.** I chose to bundle every\\n  workspace dep into `dist/cli.js` rather than ship `@slopweaver/db` etc\\n  as separate npm packages. The workspace deps are private (0.0.0,\\n  `private: true`); shipping them publicly would mean coordinated\\n  versioning across four packages on every release. With bundling, the\\n  only runtime dep is `better-sqlite3`. If you'd rather have a multi-\\n  package release flow, easy to flip — the workspace deps live in\\n  `devDependencies` already.\\n- **`bin` name vs npm package name.** `bin: { slopweaver }` so users get\\n  a `slopweaver` binary on PATH. The npm package is\\n  `@slopweaver/mcp-local`. Issue #22 left \\\"or final name TBD\\\" open —\\n  happy to rename to `slopweaver` (the package, not just the bin) if\\n  that's the call.\\n- **`private: false` + `version: 0.0.0`.** Per the issue's \\\"ready for\\n  npm publish\\\" criterion. Real version bumps will land via the\\n  `release.yml` workflow when we tag.\\n- **Smoke test scope.** It only asserts `ping` round-trips. As composite\\n  tools land, the smoke test grows alongside the registry — but the\\n  point of this PR is to prove packaging works, not to test tool logic\\n  (that's covered in `@slopweaver/mcp-server`'s in-memory test).\\n- **Out of scope per #22**: `init` / `doctor` / `connect` subcommands,\\n  web UI, real integrations. Will file follow-ups once this lands.\\n\\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\\n\\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\\n\\n* **New Features**\\n  * Added a local CLI command to run a local MCP server with DB integration and a ping tool.\\n\\n* **Documentation**\\n  * Added end-user setup, install, run, and smoke-test documentation for the local MCP binary.\\n\\n* **Tests**\\n  * Added an end-to-end smoke test validating CLI startup and ping round-trip over stdio.\\n\\n* **Chores**\\n  * Prepared several packages for public distribution and updated build/test/configuration and task pipeline.\\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\",\"reactions\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/28/reactions\",\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"timeline_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/28/timeline\",\"performed_via_github_app\":null,\"state_reason\":null,\"score\":1},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/27\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/27/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/27/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/27/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/27\",\"id\":4371537253,\"node_id\":\"PR_kwDOSSFOvc7Xwlfw\",\"number\":27,\"title\":\"feat(mcp-server): scaffold @slopweaver/mcp-server with stdio transport + ping tool\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"lachiejames\",\"id\":47808687,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3ODA4Njg3\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47808687?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/lachiejames\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[],\"state\":\"closed\",\"locked\":false,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":2,\"created_at\":\"2026-05-03T10:51:53Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-03T11:13:48Z\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-05-03T11:13:46Z\",\"assignee\":null,\"author_association\":\"MEMBER\",\"type\":null,\"active_lock_reason\":null,\"draft\":false,\"pull_request\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/pulls/27\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/27\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/27.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/27.patch\",\"merged_at\":\"2026-05-03T11:13:46Z\"},\"body\":\"## What this PR does\\n\\nScaffolds `packages/mcp-server/` — the framework-agnostic MCP server. It\\nships v1's stdio transport, a typed tool registry, the builtin `ping` tool,\\nand a Vitest test that exercises the wiring through an in-memory MCP\\ntransport.\\n\\n## Why\\n\\ncloses #21. Sequential precondition for #22 (the `apps/mcp-local` binary\\nthat wires this package into the published `slopweaver` CLI). Stdio-only,\\nno auth, per decision #11.\\n\\n## What's in the package\\n\\n- `src/server.ts` — `createMcpServer({ db, tools, version })` returns a\\n  configured `McpServer` from `@modelcontextprotocol/sdk@1.29.0` (v1.x line\\n  per the issue, not the pre-alpha v2 `main`). Each `Tool` is registered via\\n  the SDK's `registerTool` so input/output validation and JSON-Schema\\n  generation happen in the SDK.\\n- `src/tools/registry.ts` — `Tool` storage type plus `defineTool<TInput,\\n  TOutput>` for authors. The split exists because TypeScript variance forbids\\n  storing `Tool<PingArgs, PingResult>` inside `ReadonlyArray<Tool<unknown,\\n  unknown>>` directly; `defineTool` keeps strong types at the call site and\\n  erases generics at storage. Casts are sound because the SDK validates\\n  input against `inputSchema` before invoking the handler.\\n- `src/tools/builtin/ping.ts` — `createPingTool({ version, startedAtMs,\\n  now? })` returns the smoke-test tool wired to `PingArgs` / `PingResult`\\n  from `@slopweaver/contracts`. The `now` injection lets the test pin uptime\\n  deterministically.\\n- `src/transports/stdio.ts` — `startStdio({ server })` constructs a\\n  `StdioServerTransport` and connects it. Lifecycle (signals, exit codes)\\n  stays with the app layer.\\n- `src/server.test.ts` — pairs an `InMemoryTransport` with a real MCP\\n  `Client`, asserts `ping` is advertised under `tools/list`, and round-trips\\n  a `tools/call` whose `structuredContent` validates against the\\n  `PingResult` contract. A second case asserts that an unknown tool name\\n  comes back with `isError: true`.\\n\\n## Test plan\\n\\nRun from this branch:\\n\\n- [x] `pnpm format:check` — green\\n- [x] `pnpm lint` — green\\n- [x] `pnpm compile` — green\\n- [x] `pnpm test` — green (2 new tests in `@slopweaver/mcp-server`, all\\n  prior packages still passing)\\n- [x] `pnpm knip` — green (no unused exports)\\n\\n`pnpm validate` runs all five gates in sequence and is also green.\\n\\n## Breaking changes\\n\\nNone. New package; no existing consumers.\\n\\n## Notes for the reviewer\\n\\n- **`Server` vs `McpServer`** — the issue says \\\"configured MCP `Server`\\n  instance\\\". I used the SDK's high-level `McpServer` because it owns\\n  validation, JSON-Schema conversion, and tool error wrapping that we'd\\n  otherwise reimplement on top of the lower-level `Server`. `McpServer.server`\\n  exposes the underlying `Server` for advanced consumers. Easy to flip the\\n  return type if you'd rather it return `Server` literally.\\n- **Tool type erasure** — see `defineTool` rationale above. The alternative\\n  was relaxing storage to `Tool<any, any>`, which CLAUDE.md disallows.\\n- **Output schema not in the issue criteria** — the issue lists `inputSchema`\\n  + handler. I added `outputSchema` because the SDK validates\\n  `structuredContent` against it; dropping it would mean unvalidated tool\\n  output. Happy to remove if you'd rather defer until composite tools land.\\n- **No HTTP / no auth** — per #11. The SDK still pulls `express` and\\n  friends as transitive deps, but nothing in this package imports them;\\n  `apps/mcp-local` will only call `startStdio`.\\n\\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\\n\\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\\n\\n* **New Features**\\n  * New MCP server package for registering tools, running via stdio, and a builtin ping health tool.\\n* **Tests**\\n  * Integration tests for tool listing, calling, schema round-trips, and SDK-side input validation.\\n* **Documentation**\\n  * Package README documenting API surface, usage, and local development.\\n* **Chores**\\n  * Build/test config and npm scripts for local development.\\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\",\"reactions\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/27/reactions\",\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"timeline_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/27/timeline\",\"performed_via_github_app\":null,\"state_reason\":null,\"score\":1},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/26\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/26/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/26/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/26/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/26\",\"id\":4371525320,\"node_id\":\"PR_kwDOSSFOvc7XwjLs\",\"number\":26,\"title\":\"docs: rewrite README install snippet for stdio MCP flow\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"lachiejames\",\"id\":47808687,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3ODA4Njg3\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47808687?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/lachiejames\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[],\"state\":\"closed\",\"locked\":false,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":2,\"created_at\":\"2026-05-03T10:45:27Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-03T11:00:28Z\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-05-03T11:00:26Z\",\"assignee\":null,\"author_association\":\"MEMBER\",\"type\":null,\"active_lock_reason\":null,\"draft\":false,\"pull_request\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/pulls/26\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/26\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/26.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/26.patch\",\"merged_at\":\"2026-05-03T11:00:26Z\"},\"body\":\"## What this PR does\\n\\nRewrites the README's \\\"Install (coming with v1.0.0)\\\" section so it matches the resolution of #11 (stdio-only MCP transport, no MCP-layer auth). Drops the dropped commands (`slopweaver token create`, `~/.claude.json` paste) and shows the actual stdio flow Claude Code uses. Also tightens the v1.0 integration line to match the roadmap.\\n\\n## Why\\n\\nCloses #23.\\n\\nPer the resolution of #11, v1 ships stdio-only with no MCP-layer auth — no token paste required. The current README still shows the dropped flow, which would mislead anyone arriving from the roadmap or release notes. Doc-only change; can land in parallel with the v1 implementation issues (#19–22).\\n\\n## Test plan\\n\\nValidation gates (all green):\\n\\n- [x] `pnpm format:check`\\n- [x] `pnpm lint`\\n- [x] `pnpm compile`\\n- [x] `pnpm test`\\n- [x] `pnpm knip`\\n- [x] CI green\\n\\nAcceptance criteria from #23:\\n\\n- [x] Install section uses `claude mcp add slopweaver -- npx -y @slopweaver/mcp-local`\\n- [x] No `slopweaver token create`, no `~/.claude.json` paste, no OAuth 2.1 / PAT references\\n- [x] Integration list reads \\\"GitHub + Slack\\\" for v1.0 (matches roadmap)\\n- [x] Note clarifying user-to-GitHub auth is separate from MCP transport\\n- [x] Cursor / Codex / Cline get a brief pointer (full snippets deferred until v1.0.0 release, since `@slopweaver/mcp-local` isn't on npm yet)\\n\\n## Breaking changes\\n\\nNone.\\n\\n## Notes for the reviewer\\n\\n- `@slopweaver/mcp-local` isn't published yet (`npm view` 404). The section keeps the \\\"coming with v1.0.0\\\" framing on purpose — we're showing what the install *will* look like, not promising it works today.\\n- Per-client (Cursor/Cline/Codex) snippets are deferred to the v1.0.0 release rather than guessed inline. Happy to expand if you'd prefer to ship example JSON configs now.\\n\\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\\n\\n* **Documentation**\\n  * Rewrote installation to document running the tool as a local subprocess exposed to clients over stdio.\\n  * Added client-specific setup snippets and exact command/argument examples for Claude Code, Cursor, Cline, and Codex CLI.\\n  * Clarified that GitHub credentials (OAuth/PAT) are required for GitHub connections and are separate from transport auth.\\n  * Updated integrations to confirm v1.0 support for GitHub and Slack.\\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\",\"reactions\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/26/reactions\",\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"timeline_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/26/timeline\",\"performed_via_github_app\":null,\"state_reason\":null,\"score\":1},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/25\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/25/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/25/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/25/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/25\",\"id\":4371451141,\"node_id\":\"PR_kwDOSSFOvc7XwVZO\",\"number\":25,\"title\":\"feat(db): scaffold @slopweaver/db with Drizzle SQLite + initial migration\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"lachiejames\",\"id\":47808687,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3ODA4Njg3\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47808687?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/lachiejames\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[],\"state\":\"closed\",\"locked\":false,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":2,\"created_at\":\"2026-05-03T10:03:14Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-03T10:29:51Z\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-05-03T10:29:49Z\",\"assignee\":null,\"author_association\":\"MEMBER\",\"type\":null,\"active_lock_reason\":null,\"draft\":false,\"pull_request\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/pulls/25\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/25\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/25.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/25.patch\",\"merged_at\":\"2026-05-03T10:29:49Z\"},\"body\":\"## What this PR does\\n\\nAdds the persistence package: \\\\`@slopweaver/db\\\\` with Drizzle ORM + better-sqlite3, the four v1 tables (\\\\`evidence_log\\\\`, \\\\`identity_graph\\\\`, \\\\`integration_state\\\\`, \\\\`workspaces\\\\`), a generated initial migration, and a \\\\`createDb({ path })\\\\` helper that opens the DB and applies pending migrations. Default DB path is XDG-aware (\\\\`\\\\$XDG_DATA_HOME/slopweaver/slopweaver.db\\\\` if set, else \\\\`~/.slopweaver/slopweaver.db\\\\`).\\n\\n## Why\\n\\nCloses #20. The DB package is a sequential precondition for \\\\`packages/mcp-server\\\\` and the integration packages. Per the closed decision in #11 (stdio-only v1, no MCP-layer auth), there is no \\\\`mcp_tokens\\\\` / \\\\`mcp_audit_log\\\\` table. Column names align with \\\\`@slopweaver/contracts\\\\` (#19) — \\\\`integration\\\\`, \\\\`kind\\\\`, \\\\`payload_json\\\\`, \\\\`citation_url\\\\`, \\\\`occurred_at\\\\` — so consumers don't need a renaming layer between persistence and the wire.\\n\\nThe schema was planned with codex (hybrid \\\\`/codex\\\\` loop), then implemented and pinned to exact versions of \\\\`drizzle-orm\\\\` (0.45.2) and \\\\`drizzle-kit\\\\` (0.31.10) so generated migrations stay deterministic across contributors.\\n\\n## Test plan\\n\\n- [x] \\\\`pnpm format:check\\\\` ✅\\n- [x] \\\\`pnpm lint\\\\` ✅ (only pre-existing infos in cli-tools, unchanged here)\\n- [x] \\\\`pnpm compile\\\\` ✅\\n- [x] \\\\`pnpm test\\\\` ✅ (6 new tests in \\\\`@slopweaver/db\\\\`: 4 path resolver, 2 createDb integration including UNIQUE-constraint pinning)\\n- [x] \\\\`pnpm knip\\\\` ✅\\n- [x] Manual: \\\\`pnpm --filter @slopweaver/db drizzle-kit generate\\\\` is now a no-op (\\\"No schema changes, nothing to migrate\\\")\\n- [x] Manual: \\\\`pnpm install\\\\` from a clean tree builds the better-sqlite3 native binary via the new \\\\`pnpm.onlyBuiltDependencies\\\\` allowlist\\n\\n## Breaking changes\\n\\nNone.\\n\\n## Notes for the reviewer\\n\\n- **Cross-cutting change**: \\\\`packages/cli-tools/src/lib/data-dir.ts\\\\` also gets XDG support so dev tooling and product data agree on a single XDG-aware data directory. This was an explicit decision during planning.\\n- **\\\\`pnpm.onlyBuiltDependencies\\\\`**: required because pnpm 10 blocks install scripts by default; \\\\`better-sqlite3\\\\` and \\\\`esbuild\\\\` need theirs to run.\\n- **Schema ↔ contracts naming**: \\\\`evidence_log.id\\\\` is still \\\\`integer\\\\` while \\\\`EvidenceLogEntry.id\\\\` is \\\\`string\\\\` on the wire — codex flagged this during planning. Kept integer for storage efficiency; the contract layer stringifies at the boundary. Trivial to revisit.\\n- **\\\\`workspaces\\\\` is not seeded by the migration**: per Drizzle convention, migrations are tool-generated and don't include data. First writer should insert \\\\`{ id: 1, name: 'default', ... }\\\\`.\\n\\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\\n\\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\\n\\n* **New Features**\\n  * Added a new DB package for local SQLite-backed state with migrations and runtime DB creation\\n  * XDG Base Directory support for platform-standard data directory resolution\\n  * New schemas for evidence logging, identity mapping, integration state, and single-row workspace config\\n\\n* **Documentation**\\n  * Added package README with API, usage, migrations, and troubleshooting guidance\\n\\n* **Tests**\\n  * Added unit and integration tests covering path resolution, DB creation, migrations, and schema constraints\\n\\n* **Chores**\\n  * Updated gitignore and package config for build/runtime tooling\\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\",\"reactions\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/25/reactions\",\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"timeline_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/25/timeline\",\"performed_via_github_app\":null,\"state_reason\":null,\"score\":1},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/24\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/24/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/24/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/24/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/24\",\"id\":4371391628,\"node_id\":\"PR_kwDOSSFOvc7XwKo5\",\"number\":24,\"title\":\"feat(contracts): scaffold zod schemas for v1 MCP tools\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"lachiejames\",\"id\":47808687,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3ODA4Njg3\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47808687?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/lachiejames\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[],\"state\":\"closed\",\"locked\":false,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":2,\"created_at\":\"2026-05-03T09:29:58Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-03T09:49:13Z\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-05-03T09:49:10Z\",\"assignee\":null,\"author_association\":\"MEMBER\",\"type\":null,\"active_lock_reason\":null,\"draft\":false,\"pull_request\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/pulls/24\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/24\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/24.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/24.patch\",\"merged_at\":\"2026-05-03T09:49:10Z\"},\"body\":\"## What this PR does\\n\\nScaffolds the `@slopweaver/contracts` leaf package with Zod schemas for the v1 MCP tool surface. This is the type spine the rest of the v1 packages depend on.\\n\\nSchemas exported (per #19 acceptance):\\n\\n- `PingArgs` / `PingResult` — locked to `{ ok, version, uptime_s }` for #21's mcp-server\\n- `Reference` — discriminated union of `{ kind: 'url' }` and `{ kind: 'canonical', integration, id }`\\n- `Freshness` — per-integration last-poll + stale flag\\n- `EvidenceLogEntry` — DB-row-shaped record (also aligns with #20)\\n- `StartSessionArgs` / `StartSessionResult` — flagship tool I/O for #12 / `start_session()`\\n\\nStrict mode TS, named-object inputs, no `any`, no `unknown`. Pure Zod (ts-rest deferred until it pulls weight).\\n\\n## Why\\n\\ncloses #19. Sequential precondition for #20 (db), #21 (mcp-server), #22 (mcp-local — the v1 MVP install milestone).\\n\\n## Test plan\\n\\n- [x] Tests added: `src/index.test.ts` covers (1) public-surface smoke for all 7 schemas and (2) `PingResult` happy + sad path via `safeParse`\\n- [x] `pnpm validate` green locally (format/lint/compile/test/knip — five gates per the public CI)\\n- [ ] CI green (will run when this PR is converted from draft)\\n\\n## Breaking changes\\n\\nNone — new package.\\n\\n## Notes for the reviewer\\n\\n- The package stays source-first / `private: true` (matches `@slopweaver/cli-tools`); no build step, exports point at `src/index.ts`.\\n- `Reference` uses `integration` (not `platform`) to match repo language. If you'd prefer `platform`, easier to rename here than after `db` and `mcp-server` consume it.\\n- `priority` on `StartSessionItem` is a positive integer rank (1 = highest). If you want enum priorities (`high`/`medium`/`low`) instead, flag now before #20-22.\\n- `payload_json` uses a recursive `JsonObject` schema rather than `z.unknown()` — keeps the contract honest about what the DB will actually store.\\n- Pre-existing biome lint `infos` in `cli-tools/` (5 `useLiteralKeys` and a schema-version note) are intentionally **not** touched here per scope discipline; happy to file a separate cleanup issue.\\n\\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\\n\\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\\n\\n## Release Notes\\n\\n* **New Features**\\n  * Launched a new contracts package providing type-safe, validated schema definitions for API requests, responses, and data entities.\\n\\n* **Tests**\\n  * Added comprehensive test coverage for schema validation, type safety, and data conformance scenarios.\\n\\n* **Chores**\\n  * Configured package infrastructure with TypeScript support and automated testing capabilities.\\n\\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\",\"reactions\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/24/reactions\",\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"timeline_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/24/timeline\",\"performed_via_github_app\":null,\"state_reason\":null,\"score\":1},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/18\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/18/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/18/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/18/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/18\",\"id\":4371221606,\"node_id\":\"PR_kwDOSSFOvc7Xvrad\",\"number\":18,\"title\":\"feat: bring codex orchestration workflow + runner from private repo\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"lachiejames\",\"id\":47808687,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3ODA4Njg3\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47808687?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/lachiejames\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[],\"state\":\"closed\",\"locked\":false,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":2,\"created_at\":\"2026-05-03T07:57:36Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-03T09:16:47Z\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-05-03T09:16:45Z\",\"assignee\":null,\"author_association\":\"MEMBER\",\"type\":null,\"active_lock_reason\":null,\"draft\":false,\"pull_request\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/pulls/18\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/18\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/18.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/18.patch\",\"merged_at\":\"2026-05-03T09:16:45Z\"},\"body\":\"## What this PR does\\n\\nBrings the maintainer's hybrid Codex + Claude orchestration loop into the public repo:\\n\\n- New `/codex` slash command (`.claude/commands/codex.md`) — codex-agent CLI quick reference, the `await-turn` vs `capture` rule, the 5-phase flow, push discipline.\\n- New `pnpm cli orchestration prepare/run` runner — ported from `slopweaver-private` (`packages/cli-tools/src/orchestration/{core,runtime,index}.ts` + `core.test.ts`).\\n- Chain file format docs (`docs/orchestration/chain-format.md`) and a public example chain that doubles as the test fixture.\\n- Optional codex install pointer added to `docs/contributing/ai-workflow.md` (`brew install tmux`, `bun`, `@openai/codex`, `kingbootoshi/codex-orchestrator`). The existing \\\"Codex (optional)\\\" paragraph is intentionally unchanged.\\n- Small adjacent additions: `/codex` row in `.claude/rules/workflow.md`, a cross-link from `review-pr.md`, and `Bash(codex-agent:*)` + `gh run *` entries in `.claude/settings.json`.\\n- Two new lib utilities (`lib/args.ts`, `lib/colors.ts`) used by the runner.\\n\\n## Why\\n\\n`slopweaver-private` has the operational tooling for the maintainer's day-to-day workflow; the public repo only had a passing reference. This PR makes the actual workflow reproducible in public without leaking strategy or private chain content.\\n\\nThe framing in `CLAUDE.md` and the `Codex (optional)` paragraph in `ai-workflow.md` is deliberately preserved — codex stays optional for contributors. The tooling is here for those who want it.\\n\\n## Test plan\\n\\n- [x] `pnpm format:check` clean\\n- [x] `pnpm lint` clean (5 non-blocking infos on `useLiteralKeys`)\\n- [x] `pnpm compile` clean\\n- [x] `pnpm test` — 49 tests pass, including 7 new orchestration parser tests in `core.test.ts`\\n- [x] `pnpm cli orchestration run @docs/orchestration/examples/refactor-example.md --dry-run` prints the expected phase plan\\n- [ ] End-to-end run against a throwaway chain (deferred — requires `codex-agent` install)\\n\\n## Breaking changes\\n\\nNone.\\n\\n## Notes for the reviewer\\n\\n- `runtime.ts` is a verbatim port of ~1300 lines from the private runner, with two changes: import paths swapped from `@/` aliases to relative `./` paths, and `pnpm cli worktree new` updated to `pnpm cli worktree-new` to match the public CLI shape.\\n- The CLI command is a single `orchestration <subcommand> <chainPath>` with internal subcommand routing. cac doesn't natively support multi-word commands; registering `orchestration prepare` and `orchestration run` separately collided.\\n- Resource-limit / RAM / port-conflict rules from the private `worktree-patterns.md` are NOT ported. Public repo has no expensive commands yet and adding rules for problems we don't have is premature.\\n- Draft-PR convention from private is also NOT ported per locked decision; public CI is free-tier.\",\"reactions\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/18/reactions\",\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"timeline_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/18/timeline\",\"performed_via_github_app\":null,\"state_reason\":null,\"score\":1},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/17\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/17/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/17/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/17/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/17\",\"id\":4371170598,\"node_id\":\"PR_kwDOSSFOvc7Xvh-5\",\"number\":17,\"title\":\"chore: add knip + pnpm validate + .editorconfig\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"lachiejames\",\"id\":47808687,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3ODA4Njg3\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47808687?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/lachiejames\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[],\"state\":\"closed\",\"locked\":false,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":0,\"created_at\":\"2026-05-03T07:28:50Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-03T07:40:48Z\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-05-03T07:40:46Z\",\"assignee\":null,\"author_association\":\"MEMBER\",\"type\":null,\"active_lock_reason\":null,\"draft\":false,\"pull_request\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/pulls/17\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/17\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/17.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/17.patch\",\"merged_at\":\"2026-05-03T07:40:46Z\"},\"body\":\"## What this PR does\\n\\nAdds three small tooling pieces from #10's checklist: **Knip 6.7.0** for unused-export/dependency detection, a **`pnpm validate`** umbrella script that mirrors CI in one shot, and **`.editorconfig`** so non-Biome editors get the right indentation and line endings out of the box. Wires Knip into CI between `Lint` and `Compile`.\\n\\n## Why\\n\\nThree separate items on the Scaffolding & DevOps tracking issue, all small enough that splitting them into three PRs would be churn. Each is independent and zero-risk: Knip catches dead code/deps before merge, `pnpm validate` gives one command that locally reproduces CI, and `.editorconfig` is purely defensive against editors that don't speak Biome.\\n\\nrefs #10\\n\\n## Tooling decision (deferred items)\\n\\nConsidered but **deliberately skipped** in this PR:\\n\\n- **Oxlint** — the private repo runs a 3-tier chain (Biome → Oxlint → ESLint). At this repo's size (~15 source files in one package), the rule-overlap suppression dance costs more than it saves. Revisit once ESLint runtime becomes a measurable bottleneck or the second package lands.\\n- **Prettier** — Biome 2.x already formats Markdown; the only YAML files here are stable CI workflows. Adding Prettier just to format YAML isn't worth a new tool.\\n- **Lefthook / git hooks** — nice-to-have; can land later as a separate item.\\n\\nIf those calls turn out wrong, they're all reversible without touching this PR.\\n\\n## Knip config\\n\\nStarted minimal:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"$schema\\\": \\\"https://unpkg.com/knip@6/schema.json\\\",\\n  \\\"ignoreExportsUsedInFile\\\": {\\n    \\\"type\\\": true\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n`ignoreExportsUsedInFile.type=true` lets us export types like `RunDoctorDeps` / `WorktreePlan` for documentation/future-test consumption without Knip flagging them. Value exports are still policed normally — only types-used-in-their-own-file get the pass. No aggressive ignore list yet; the private repo's 30+ ignores were tuned over time and would be premature noise here.\\n\\n## Test plan\\n\\n- [x] `pnpm format:check` ✅\\n- [x] `pnpm lint` ✅\\n- [x] `pnpm compile` ✅\\n- [x] `pnpm test` ✅ (42 tests in cli-tools)\\n- [x] `pnpm knip` ✅ (clean)\\n- [x] `pnpm validate` ✅ (full chain green end-to-end)\\n- [x] CI will run the new `Knip` step on this PR\\n\\n## Breaking changes\\n\\nNone.\\n\\n## Notes for the reviewer\\n\\n- `.editorconfig` mirrors `biome.json`'s formatting (2-space indent, LF, UTF-8) — no new opinions, just exposes existing ones to non-Biome editors.\\n- The `validate` script chains with `&&`, so it stops at the first failure and surfaces the offending check directly. No fancy reporting wrapper needed.\\n- Knip step in CI is positioned **after** Lint and **before** Compile to keep \\\"fast checks first\\\" — Knip is fast, and failing on dead code before paying the TS compile cost is cheap signal.\\n- Three checkboxes on #10 to tick on merge: `pnpm cli doctor` ✅ already, plus the three from this PR (`Knip`, `validate`, `.editorconfig`).\\n\\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\",\"reactions\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/17/reactions\",\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"timeline_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/17/timeline\",\"performed_via_github_app\":null,\"state_reason\":null,\"score\":1},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/16\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/16/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/16/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/16/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/16\",\"id\":4371040614,\"node_id\":\"PR_kwDOSSFOvc7XvKBE\",\"number\":16,\"title\":\"feat(cli-tools): add `pnpm cli doctor` + Vitest scaffolding\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"lachiejames\",\"id\":47808687,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3ODA4Njg3\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47808687?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/lachiejames\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[],\"state\":\"closed\",\"locked\":false,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":0,\"created_at\":\"2026-05-03T06:14:23Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-03T07:00:57Z\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-05-03T07:00:55Z\",\"assignee\":null,\"author_association\":\"MEMBER\",\"type\":null,\"active_lock_reason\":null,\"draft\":false,\"pull_request\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/pulls/16\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/16\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/16.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/16.patch\",\"merged_at\":\"2026-05-03T07:00:55Z\"},\"body\":\"## What this PR does\\n\\nAdds the first interactive subcommand to `@slopweaver/cli-tools` -- `pnpm cli doctor` -- and stands up the Vitest infrastructure that future subcommands will hang off. Backfills the existing `worktree` subcommand to the same testable pattern and fixes the `cac` multi-word dispatch issue along the way (renaming `worktree new` -> `worktree-new`).\\n\\n`doctor` runs four environment checks (Node ≥22, pnpm ≥10, port 60701 free, `~/.slopweaver/` data dir writable) and prompts interactively to create the data dir if it's missing. Exits 0 on success or warnings-only, 1 on failure.\\n\\n## Why\\n\\nSub-task of #10 (Scaffolding & DevOps tracking) -- knocks off two of its checklist items in one PR (`pnpm cli doctor` + Vitest scaffolding for cli-tools) and incidentally fixes #15 (the silent `worktree new` cac bug) by renaming the broken multi-word command. Establishes the testable + interactive subcommand pattern the next round of subcommands (e.g. `connect-local`) will follow.\\n\\ncloses #12\\ncloses #15\\nrefs #10\\n\\n## Test plan\\n\\n- [x] **42 unit tests** across 6 colocated `*.test.ts` files (sanitiseTaskName + plan, paths, data-dir, all 4 doctor checks, runDoctor orchestrator, runWorktreeNew orchestrator)\\n- [x] Manually verified end-to-end via `expect`-driven PTY: doctor's all-green path, missing-data-dir prompt → accept (dir created), prompt → decline (warning summary), and exit-code-1 fail path\\n- [x] CI green locally:\\n  - `pnpm format:check` ✓\\n  - `pnpm lint` ✓\\n  - `pnpm compile` ✓\\n  - `pnpm test` ✓ (42 tests, ~1.1s)\\n- [x] Smoke-tested `pnpm cli worktree-new` -- action callback now fires (was silently broken before #15)\\n- [x] Single squashed commit\\n\\n## Breaking changes\\n\\n`pnpm cli worktree new` -> `pnpm cli worktree-new`. The old multi-word form never actually worked (cac 7.0.0 doesn't dispatch multi-word commands -- silent exit 0), so this is fixing rather than breaking. All in-repo references updated (workflow rule, slash command, AI workflow doc, package README).\\n\\n## Notes for the reviewer\\n\\n**Conventions established** (worth pushing back on if you'd rather differ):\\n- Tests colocated as `*.test.ts` next to the file under test (vs. private repo's `__tests__/` layout). Colocation is more discoverable for a package this size and matches modern Vitest defaults.\\n- Pure logic in sibling files (`checks.ts`, `plan.ts`); orchestrators (`index.ts`) inject all I/O (`prompt`, `mkdir`, `exec`, `tryBind`, `getVersion`, `log`) so they're testable without module mocking.\\n- Orchestrators return `{ ok, exitCode }`; the dispatcher in `cli.ts` owns `process.exit`. Keeps fail paths unit-testable.\\n- Single-word command names only -- cac 7.0.0 doesn't dispatch multi-word.\\n\\n**Codex review addressed** -- ran a Codex review pass against the squashed PR. Findings actioned in this same PR:\\n- *Directory check in `checkDataDir`* -- previously a regular file at `~/.slopweaver` would falsely pass; now `statSync` confirms it's a directory.\\n- *Subprocess timeout for `checkPnpmVersion`* -- 5s timeout via `spawnSync({ timeout })`; typed `GetVersionResult` distinguishes not-found / timeout / error.\\n- *`checkPortFree` error mapping* -- `EADDRINUSE` only triggers the \\\"port in use\\\" phrasing; other codes (`EACCES` etc.) surface their actual code.\\n- *Race in port test* -- replaced ephemeral-port trick with injected `tryBind` stub; both branches now deterministic.\\n- *`process.exit` inside `runDoctor`* -- removed; orchestrator returns a result, dispatcher exits.\\n\\n**Deliberately NOT in this PR**:\\n- Auto-fix mode beyond the data-dir prompt\\n- Root-level Vitest config (per-package is fine for one package)\\n- `--json` output flag\\n- npm-publish decision (still open in #10)\\n- Doctor data dir is `~/.slopweaver/` cross-platform (not XDG/AppData) -- easier to document and debug for v1; can move to platform-native paths later if anyone asks.\\n\\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\",\"reactions\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/16/reactions\",\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"timeline_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/16/timeline\",\"performed_via_github_app\":null,\"state_reason\":null,\"score\":1},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/14\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/14/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/14/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/14/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/14\",\"id\":4371006309,\"node_id\":\"PR_kwDOSSFOvc7XvD15\",\"number\":14,\"title\":\"ci: add release.yml for npm publish on GitHub Release\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"lachiejames\",\"id\":47808687,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3ODA4Njg3\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47808687?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/lachiejames\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[],\"state\":\"closed\",\"locked\":false,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":0,\"created_at\":\"2026-05-03T05:55:42Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-03T07:00:14Z\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-05-03T07:00:13Z\",\"assignee\":null,\"author_association\":\"MEMBER\",\"type\":null,\"active_lock_reason\":null,\"draft\":false,\"pull_request\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/pulls/14\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/14\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/14.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/14.patch\",\"merged_at\":\"2026-05-03T07:00:13Z\"},\"body\":\"## What this PR does\\n\\nAdds `.github/workflows/release.yml` — a GitHub Actions workflow that publishes any non-private workspace package to npm when a GitHub Release is published. Also adds `RELEASING.md` as a human-facing runbook for the per-release flow.\\n\\n## Why\\n\\nSub-task of the Scaffolding & DevOps tracking issue (refs #10), filed as #13. Scaffold the publish pipeline now while the repo is small and there's nothing real at risk, so the moment a package flips from `private: true` to publishable, cutting a release is one click — not a mad scramble to write CI under deadline.\\n\\nThe workflow is **dormant**: `pnpm -r publish` automatically skips packages with `\\\"private\\\": true`, so today it's a safe no-op. No package is flipped public in this PR (that's the open decision still on #10).\\n\\ncloses #13\\nrefs #10\\n\\n## Test plan\\n\\n- [x] `pnpm format:check` ✓\\n- [x] `pnpm lint` ✓\\n- [x] `pnpm compile` ✓\\n- [x] `pnpm test` ✓\\n- [ ] Post-merge: trigger the workflow manually with `dry_run` checked. Expect: install + four CI gates pass + `pnpm -r publish --dry-run` reports nothing-to-publish (every package is `private: true`).\\n- [ ] Post-merge (founder, separately): create the `npm-publish` GitHub environment with `@lachiejames` as required reviewer; configure npm Trusted Publisher when the first package is ready to go public.\\n\\n## Breaking changes\\n\\nNone.\\n\\n## Notes for the reviewer\\n\\n**Security shape (deliberate choices):**\\n\\n- Pinned action SHAs (with version comment), not tag refs — defends against compromised tag re-points. Existing `ci.yml` uses `@v4` tag refs; if you'd like, I can land a follow-up PR to pin those too. I left `ci.yml` alone here to keep this PR scoped.\\n- `permissions: contents: read, id-token: write` — `id-token: write` is required by both npm provenance and Trusted Publisher OIDC, so we don't need a long-lived `NPM_TOKEN` repo secret.\\n- `environment: npm-publish` — manual approval gate (configured in repo settings; documented in `RELEASING.md`). Belt + braces with the GitHub Release UI checkpoint.\\n- `concurrency: cancel-in-progress: false` — never abort a release mid-publish.\\n\\n**Trigger model:**\\n\\n- `release: [published]` is the primary trigger. The Release page's auto-generated changelog becomes our v1 changelog (no separate CHANGELOG tooling).\\n- `workflow_dispatch` with `dry_run: true` default lets us exercise the full pipeline without touching npm.\\n\\n**Out of scope (genuinely):**\\n\\n- Changesets / release-please / version-bump tooling — manual `pnpm version` is correct for one publishable package.\\n- `CHANGELOG.md` — GitHub Release notes serve that role for v1.\\n- Slack / Sentry / smoke-test post-publish steps.\\n- GitHub Packages mirror (confirmed not wanted).\\n- Flipping `@slopweaver/cli-tools` to public — that's the decision still open on #10.\\n\\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\",\"reactions\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/14/reactions\",\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"timeline_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/14/timeline\",\"performed_via_github_app\":null,\"state_reason\":null,\"score\":1},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/7\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/7/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/7/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/7/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/7\",\"id\":4367646926,\"node_id\":\"PR_kwDOSSFOvc7XlKL0\",\"number\":7,\"title\":\"feat(contracts): add @slopweaver/contracts package with MCP token Zod schemas\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"lachiejames\",\"id\":47808687,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3ODA4Njg3\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47808687?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/lachiejames\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[],\"state\":\"closed\",\"locked\":false,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":1,\"created_at\":\"2026-05-02T02:46:13Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-03T05:53:47Z\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-05-02T03:26:56Z\",\"assignee\":null,\"author_association\":\"MEMBER\",\"type\":null,\"active_lock_reason\":null,\"draft\":false,\"pull_request\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/pulls/7\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/7\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/7.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/7.patch\",\"merged_at\":null},\"body\":\"Per v1.0.0 roadmap (#2). First real package — minimal warm-up that validates the workspace mechanics end-to-end (Turbo discovery, TS project compilation, workspace import resolution, CI gating).\\n\\n| File | Purpose |\\n|---|---|\\n| `packages/contracts/package.json` | `@slopweaver/contracts` (private). NodeNext ESM. Single dep: `zod ^4`. |\\n| `packages/contracts/tsconfig.json` | Extends `../../tsconfig.base.json`. outDir → `dist/`, rootDir → `src/`. |\\n| `packages/contracts/src/index.ts` | Re-exports from `mcp/token`. |\\n| `packages/contracts/src/mcp/token.ts` | Zod schemas for MCP token CRUD (token format regex, persisted record shape, create input/response, list response). Matches what PR503-REFERENCE-NOTES.md (private repo) describes for the upcoming `packages/auth` work. |\\n\\nts-rest contract definitions land later when `apps/cloud/` adds the REST endpoints they describe.\\n\\n**Local verification** (the same 4 checks CI runs):\\n- `pnpm format:check` ✅\\n- `pnpm lint` ✅\\n- `pnpm compile` ✅ (Turbo discovers + builds `@slopweaver/contracts`)\\n- `pnpm test` ✅ (placeholder)\\n\\n**Test plan**: CI must pass on this PR. After merge, the next package PR (`packages/env/` or `packages/db/`) can import from `@slopweaver/contracts` to verify cross-package workspace resolution works.\",\"reactions\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/7/reactions\",\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"timeline_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/7/timeline\",\"performed_via_github_app\":null,\"state_reason\":null,\"score\":1},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/9\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/9/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/9/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/9/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/9\",\"id\":4367848446,\"node_id\":\"PR_kwDOSSFOvc7Xlzcx\",\"number\":9,\"title\":\"docs(scaffolding): add .claude/ orchestration + task / decision-record templates\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"lachiejames\",\"id\":47808687,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3ODA4Njg3\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47808687?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/lachiejames\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[],\"state\":\"closed\",\"locked\":false,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":0,\"created_at\":\"2026-05-02T04:08:13Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-02T04:08:35Z\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-05-02T04:08:33Z\",\"assignee\":null,\"author_association\":\"MEMBER\",\"type\":null,\"active_lock_reason\":null,\"draft\":false,\"pull_request\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/pulls/9\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/9\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/9.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/9.patch\",\"merged_at\":\"2026-05-02T04:08:33Z\"},\"body\":\"Per v1.0.0 roadmap (#2). Foundational AI-orchestration scaffolding — public, visible, \\\"see how this project actually thinks\\\" flex for the senior IC engineer audience.\\n\\n| Path | Purpose |\\n|---|---|\\n| `.claude/settings.json` | Allowlist common Bash commands to reduce agent permission prompts |\\n| `.claude/rules/workflow.md` | Worktree convention, branch naming, squash-merge, four-CI-check rule, decisions-in-issues |\\n| `.claude/rules/pr-conventions.md` | Conventional-commits titles, template sections, size + scope discipline |\\n| `.claude/commands/fix-issue.md` | `/fix-issue <url>`: read → worktree → implement → PR (the default flow) |\\n| `.claude/commands/investigate.md` | `/investigate <topic>`: research-only, output as decision-record comment or doc |\\n| `.claude/commands/review-pr.md` | `/review-pr <url>`: second-opinion review (optional Codex) |\\n| `.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/task.yml` | AI-actionable work units with embedded `/fix-issue` prompt |\\n| `.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/decision_record.yml` | Design decisions deliberated in public; closing comment = resolution |\\n| `docs/contributing/ai-workflow.md` | Human-readable explainer for the whole loop |\\n\\n**What this enables**: every future task can be filed as an issue with the embedded `/fix-issue` prompt; agents pick it up; PRs flow through with CI gating; founder reviews + merges. Decisions get filed as `decision-record` issues with deliberation in comments — public alternative to a private DECISIONS.md.\\n\\n**Smoke tested locally** (no source changes; pure docs PR):\\n- `pnpm format:check` ✅\\n- `pnpm lint` ✅\\n- `pnpm compile` ✅ (Turbo full cache hit)\\n- `pnpm test` ✅\",\"reactions\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/9/reactions\",\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"timeline_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/9/timeline\",\"performed_via_github_app\":null,\"state_reason\":null,\"score\":1},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/8\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/8/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/8/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/8/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/8\",\"id\":4367835242,\"node_id\":\"PR_kwDOSSFOvc7Xlwue\",\"number\":8,\"title\":\"feat(cli-tools): add @slopweaver/cli-tools with worktree subcommand\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"lachiejames\",\"id\":47808687,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3ODA4Njg3\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47808687?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/lachiejames\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[],\"state\":\"closed\",\"locked\":false,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":0,\"created_at\":\"2026-05-02T04:02:52Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-02T04:03:14Z\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-05-02T04:03:12Z\",\"assignee\":null,\"author_association\":\"MEMBER\",\"type\":null,\"active_lock_reason\":null,\"draft\":false,\"pull_request\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/pulls/8\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/8\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/8.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/8.patch\",\"merged_at\":\"2026-05-02T04:03:12Z\"},\"body\":\"Per v1.0.0 roadmap (#2). First real package — and the AI-orchestration foundation that PR #9's slash commands will depend on.\\n\\n| File | Purpose |\\n|---|---|\\n| `packages/cli-tools/package.json` | @slopweaver/cli-tools, ESM, dep: `cac` 7 (modern arg parser) |\\n| `packages/cli-tools/tsconfig.json` | noEmit + allowImportingTsExtensions (tsx runs source) |\\n| `packages/cli-tools/src/cli.ts` | Entry point with cac-based subcommand dispatcher |\\n| `packages/cli-tools/src/worktree/index.ts` | Adapted from private repo. Creates worktree from origin/main on branch `worktree/<name>`, installs deps |\\n| `packages/cli-tools/src/lib/paths.ts` | `findMonorepoRoot`, `resolveWorktreesRoot` |\\n| `packages/cli-tools/README.md` | Usage + how to add subcommands |\\n\\nAlso incorporates **dep bumps from PR #7 review** in the same touch of root `package.json`:\\n- Added `cli` script (`tsx packages/cli-tools/src/cli.ts`)\\n- @biomejs/biome 2.4.13 → 2.4.14\\n- eslint 10.2.1 → 10.3.0\\n- turbo 2.9.6 → 2.9.7\\n- Added tsx 4.21.0 + @types/node 22.10.5\\n- All exact-pinned (no caret ranges)\\n\\n**Why cli-tools first (vs contracts)**: PR #9 lands `.claude/commands/fix-issue.md` which needs to invoke worktree creation. cli-tools is the dependency.\\n\\n**Why not connect-local**: 600+ lines in private, depends on Supabase + Polly cassette infra that doesn't exist in public repo yet.\\n\\n**Smoke tested locally**: `pnpm cli --help` ✅, `pnpm cli worktree --help` ✅, `pnpm format:check` ✅, `pnpm lint` ✅, `pnpm compile` ✅ (typechecks clean), `pnpm test` ✅\",\"reactions\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/8/reactions\",\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"timeline_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/8/timeline\",\"performed_via_github_app\":null,\"state_reason\":null,\"score\":1},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/6\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/6/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/6/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/6/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/6\",\"id\":4367635742,\"node_id\":\"PR_kwDOSSFOvc7XlH2b\",\"number\":6,\"title\":\"ci: add GitHub Actions workflow + initial pnpm-lock.yaml\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"lachiejames\",\"id\":47808687,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3ODA4Njg3\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47808687?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/lachiejames\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[],\"state\":\"closed\",\"locked\":false,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":0,\"created_at\":\"2026-05-02T02:42:14Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-02T02:44:36Z\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-05-02T02:44:34Z\",\"assignee\":null,\"author_association\":\"MEMBER\",\"type\":null,\"active_lock_reason\":null,\"draft\":false,\"pull_request\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/pulls/6\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/6\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/6.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/6.patch\",\"merged_at\":\"2026-05-02T02:44:34Z\"},\"body\":\"Per v1.0.0 roadmap (#2). Adds CI gating for every subsequent code PR, plus the first `pnpm-lock.yaml` generated by running `pnpm install` at the workspace root.\\n\\n**.github/workflows/ci.yml** — push-to-main + PR triggers; ubuntu-latest; concurrency cancellation; `contents: read` permissions; setup pnpm + Node 22 (from .nvmrc) with pnpm cache; `pnpm install --frozen-lockfile` then `format:check` → `lint` → `compile` → `test`.\\n\\n**pnpm-lock.yaml** — first lockfile. Required for `--frozen-lockfile` in CI.\\n\\n**biome.json** — tiny formatting nit (one-line vs multi-line array per Biome's 100-col preference) auto-fixed during local smoke testing.\\n\\n`compile` and `test` pass trivially today (no packages defining those tasks yet). They become real gates as soon as PR #6+ adds the first package.\\n\\nSmoke-tested locally before push:\\n- `pnpm format:check` ✅\\n- `pnpm lint` ✅ (1 info note about `biome migrate`, non-blocking)\\n- `pnpm compile` ✅ (0 tasks)\\n- `pnpm test` ✅ (0 tasks)\",\"reactions\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/6/reactions\",\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"timeline_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/6/timeline\",\"performed_via_github_app\":null,\"state_reason\":null,\"score\":1},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/5\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/5/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/5/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/5/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/5\",\"id\":4367624176,\"node_id\":\"PR_kwDOSSFOvc7XlFa5\",\"number\":5,\"title\":\"chore: workspace bootstrap (pnpm + Turbo + TS + Biome + ESLint boundaries)\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"lachiejames\",\"id\":47808687,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3ODA4Njg3\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47808687?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/lachiejames\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[],\"state\":\"closed\",\"locked\":false,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":0,\"created_at\":\"2026-05-02T02:37:21Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-02T02:38:28Z\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-05-02T02:38:27Z\",\"assignee\":null,\"author_association\":\"MEMBER\",\"type\":null,\"active_lock_reason\":null,\"draft\":false,\"pull_request\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/pulls/5\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/5\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/5.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/5.patch\",\"merged_at\":\"2026-05-02T02:38:27Z\"},\"body\":\"Per v1.0.0 roadmap (#2). 7 root-level config files; no actual code yet — the workspace is empty until the first package PR lands.\\n\\n| File | Purpose |\\n|---|---|\\n| `.nvmrc` | Node 22 |\\n| `pnpm-workspace.yaml` | Declares `apps/*` and `packages/*` as workspaces |\\n| `package.json` | Workspace root; pnpm@10 + Node >=22 pinned; Biome / ESLint / Turbo / TS devdeps |\\n| `turbo.json` | build / compile / lint / test / dev pipeline tasks |\\n| `tsconfig.base.json` | Strict TS config (NodeNext, noUncheckedIndexedAccess, exactOptionalPropertyTypes, verbatimModuleSyntax) |\\n| `biome.json` | Formatter + linter; single quotes, 100-col, LF, vcs-aware |\\n| `eslint.config.js` | Two architectural rules: `eslint-plugin-boundaries` (apps→packages allowed; packages→apps forbidden) + `no-restricted-imports` (no `@nestjs/*` in packages) |\\n\\nDoesn't try to install anything, doesn't add CI workflows. Both arrive in subsequent PRs once there's something to install / test.\",\"reactions\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/5/reactions\",\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"timeline_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/5/timeline\",\"performed_via_github_app\":null,\"state_reason\":null,\"score\":1},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/4\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/4/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/4/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/4/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/4\",\"id\":4367615650,\"node_id\":\"PR_kwDOSSFOvc7XlDrU\",\"number\":4,\"title\":\"docs: add CONTRIBUTING, CODE_OF_CONDUCT, issue + PR templates\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"lachiejames\",\"id\":47808687,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3ODA4Njg3\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47808687?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/lachiejames\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[],\"state\":\"closed\",\"locked\":false,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":0,\"created_at\":\"2026-05-02T02:33:36Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-02T02:38:16Z\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-05-02T02:38:15Z\",\"assignee\":null,\"author_association\":\"MEMBER\",\"type\":null,\"active_lock_reason\":null,\"draft\":false,\"pull_request\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/pulls/4\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/4\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/4.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/4.patch\",\"merged_at\":\"2026-05-02T02:38:15Z\"},\"body\":\"Governance round per v1.0.0 roadmap (#2). 7 files (~254 lines).\\n\\n**CONTRIBUTING.md** — engagement channels, \\\"open an Issue before writing code\\\" rule for non-trivial PRs, code style, best-effort review timeline.\\n\\n**CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md** — adopts Contributor Covenant 2.1 by reference (linked, not inlined). Reports to admin@slopweaver.ai.\\n\\n**Issue templates** (3 + config):\\n- `bug_report.yml` — structured form\\n- `feature_request.yml` — with willingness-to-contribute dropdown\\n- `integration_request.yml` — platform-add requests\\n- `config.yml` — disables blank issues; routes questions to Discussions and security to Private Vulnerability Reporting\\n\\n**PR template** — standard what / why / test plan structure.\",\"reactions\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/4/reactions\",\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"timeline_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/4/timeline\",\"performed_via_github_app\":null,\"state_reason\":null,\"score\":1},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/3\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/3/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/3/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/3/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/3\",\"id\":4367596770,\"node_id\":\"PR_kwDOSSFOvc7Xk_wK\",\"number\":3,\"title\":\"docs: fix tracking issue link (#1 → #2)\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"lachiejames\",\"id\":47808687,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3ODA4Njg3\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47808687?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/lachiejames\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[],\"state\":\"closed\",\"locked\":false,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":0,\"created_at\":\"2026-05-02T02:26:43Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-02T02:26:57Z\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-05-02T02:26:56Z\",\"assignee\":null,\"author_association\":\"MEMBER\",\"type\":null,\"active_lock_reason\":null,\"draft\":false,\"pull_request\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/pulls/3\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/3\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/3.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/3.patch\",\"merged_at\":\"2026-05-02T02:26:55Z\"},\"body\":\"PR #1 consumed the #1 number; the actual tracking issue is #2. Also tightened CLAUDE.md's one-line description to match the start_session hook in README.\",\"reactions\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/3/reactions\",\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"timeline_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/3/timeline\",\"performed_via_github_app\":null,\"state_reason\":null,\"score\":1},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/1\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/1/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/1/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/1/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/1\",\"id\":4367586301,\"node_id\":\"PR_kwDOSSFOvc7Xk9qw\",\"number\":1,\"title\":\"docs: add CLAUDE.md, SECURITY.md, expand README\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"lachiejames\",\"id\":47808687,\"node_id\":\"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3ODA4Njg3\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47808687?v=4\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/lachiejames\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lachiejames/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"user_view_type\":\"public\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[],\"state\":\"closed\",\"locked\":false,\"assignees\":[],\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":0,\"created_at\":\"2026-05-02T02:22:35Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-02T02:24:22Z\",\"closed_at\":\"2026-05-02T02:24:20Z\",\"assignee\":null,\"author_association\":\"MEMBER\",\"type\":null,\"active_lock_reason\":null,\"draft\":false,\"pull_request\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/pulls/1\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/1\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/1.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/slopweaver/slopweaver/pull/1.patch\",\"merged_at\":\"2026-05-02T02:24:20Z\"},\"body\":\"First content PR after the bootstrap commit. Three small governance docs:\\n\\n**README.md** — replaces the placeholder with a real first-impression page. New hook (\\\"Help Claude Code answer 'what should I work on next?'\\\"), session-start scenario as the demo, why-local-first, integrations list, link to roadmap tracking issue.\\n\\n**CLAUDE.md** — new (~60 lines). Repo state, target stack, where things will live, dev principles (direct imports, package boundaries, no NestJS in packages, small focused PRs), security/privacy reminders, note that strategy docs live in a private repo.\\n\\n**SECURITY.md** — new (~90 lines). Coordinated disclosure with the WHY up front. Primary channel is GitHub's private vulnerability reporting (already enabled). Alternative: admin@slopweaver.ai. 5/30/90 day timelines as best-effort. Public Security Advisories published once fixes ship.\\n\\nVoice convention across all three: first-person (\\\"I\\\") for personal commitments; \\\"SlopWeaver\\\" for project-level policies; no \\\"we\\\" / \\\"our\\\" / \\\"us\\\" — solo founder.\",\"reactions\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/1/reactions\",\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"timeline_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/slopweaver/slopweaver/issues/1/timeline\",\"performed_via_github_app\":null,\"state_reason\":null,\"score\":1}],\"search_type\":\"lexical\"}"
